"Roger Fagerheim is inquiring about the deadline for comments on the Fjellheisen regulatory plan in an email to Margareth Sundf\u00f8r.Troms and Finnmark County Municipality provides guidance and assistance to municipalities in their planning tasks, particularly in areas such as cultural heritage, environment, outdoor activities, housing, and transportation planning. They also consider factors such as public health, sustainability goals, and climate legislation in their assessment of planning matters. The municipality has coordinated their response regarding the detailed regulation plan for the Fjellheisen upper station in Troms\u00f8 municipality.\n\nPlanen er \u00e5 regulere etablert arealbruk av Fjellheisen p\u00e5 \u00f8vre stasjon og Fjellstua samt legge til rette for nybygg. Planen omfatter ogs\u00e5 opparbeiding av uteromsarealene mot Storsteinen. Tiltaket er vurdert \u00e5 ikke ha vesentlige virkninger for milj\u00f8 eller samfunn sammenlignet med dagens situasjon. Fylkeskommunen minner om \u00e5 ta klimahensyn i planleggingen, inkludert reduksjon av klimagassutslipp og tilpasning til klimaendringer. De ber om en beskrivelse av tiltakets klimagassutslipp og vurdering av p\u00e5virkning p\u00e5 klimatilpasning. Det antas at eksisterende bygningsmasse skal rives.\n\nTroms and Finnmark County Council must provide input on the development of a new building and the demolition of an existing one in Troms\u00f8 municipality. They must consider various aspects such as cultural heritage, environment, landscape, outdoor activities, housing, transportation, shopping centers, and public health in their planning. The council's decision-making is also guided by the UN's sustainable development goals and climate considerations. The deadline for their response is February 15, 2023.\n\nPlanen omfatter regulering av etablert arealbruk av Fjellheisen og Fjellstua, samt legge til rette for nybygg og opparbeidelse av uteromsarealene mot Storsteinen. Planomr\u00e5det er ikke detaljregulert og omfattes av LNFR-form\u00e5let i kommuneplanens arealdel. Tiltaket er vurdert \u00e5 ikke ha vesentlige virkninger for milj\u00f8 eller samfunn. Fylkeskommunen p\u00e5peker viktigheten av \u00e5 ta klimahensyn og ber om at tiltakets klimagassutslipp og p\u00e5virkning p\u00e5 klimatilpasning beskrives i planbeskrivelsen. Det antas at eksisterende bygningsmasse skal rives i forbindelse med planen.\n\nThe demolition of existing buildings and materials for a new building will require transportation of large quantities of materials to and from the Fjellheisplat\u00e5et. The plan should specify how this will be carried out. The area is within a cultural heritage area of national interest and must be designated as such. Specific regulations must be developed in consultation with the Sami Parliament. The area around the mountain lift station and restaurant should be designated as a building area, with specific regulations based on the existing building permit. Some of the outdoor areas should be designated as green space and recreational areas with pathways and fences, with regulations ensuring minimal visual impact.\n\nFylkeskommunen \u00f8nsker at tiltak p\u00e5 fjellheisplat\u00e5et i Troms\u00f8 i minst mulig grad skal v\u00e6re synlige fra selve Troms\u00f8ya, bortsett fra stasjonen. Omr\u00e5der som ikke skal tilrettelegges b\u00f8r brukes til LNFR-form\u00e5l. De ber om uttalelse om samiske kulturminner fra Sametinget. Fjellstua ligger i et viktig friluftslivsomr\u00e5de med h\u00f8y brukerfrekvens, og det er viktig at en eventuell moderne fjellstue tilpasses landskapet og allmennhetens opplevelse. Fylkeskommunen mener det b\u00f8r legges til hel\u00e5rige toalettl\u00f8sninger for allmennheten og understreker tiltakshavers ansvar for omr\u00e5dene rundt Fjellstua.\n\nFylkeskommunen mener det er behov for bedre bes\u00f8ksforvaltning p\u00e5 Fjellheisplat\u00e5et p\u00e5 grunn av slitasje og manglende tilrettelegging. De \u00f8nsker en helhetlig strategisk tiln\u00e6rming med fokus p\u00e5 b\u00e6rekraft og hensyn til naturen og bes\u00f8kende. De p\u00e5peker ogs\u00e5 viktigheten av tiltakshaveres ansvar for omliggende omr\u00e5der. Fylkeskommunen er uenig i avgrensningen av planen og mener viktige sp\u00f8rsm\u00e5l som infrastruktur og parkering b\u00f8r reguleres i denne prosessen. Avslutningsvis oppfordrer de til samarbeid og \u00f8nsker lykke til med planarbeidet.HAMRAN/JOHANSEN ARKITEKTER AS has submitted a plan initiative for detailed regulation of new construction for Fjellstua and outdoor areas on properties 17/1473, 1475, 1, 6, and 11 on behalf of Fjellheisen AS. The plan initiative aims to establish the framework and process for private detailed regulation. The previous process involved submitting an application for a framework permit with a dispensation from the LNFR area purpose on October 15, 2020, which was sent for limited consultation with relevant sector authorities.\n\nTroms\u00f8 kommune godkjente et byggeprosjekt med dispensasjon under betingelse av en avtale om prosjektering og opparbeidelse av utend\u00f8rsomr\u00e5der. Etter endringer i eierskapet, ble nye eiere n\u00f8dt til \u00e5 gjennomf\u00f8re en detaljregulering av prosjektet. Form\u00e5let med planen er \u00e5 bekrefte arealbruk og muliggj\u00f8re opparbeidelse av utend\u00f8rsarealer, basert p\u00e5 samarbeid med kommunen. Planen ble initiert som en s\u00f8knad om rammetillatelse med dispensasjon fra naturvernomr\u00e5der, og ble sendt til relevante myndigheter for h\u00f8ring.\n\nTroms\u00f8 kommune godkjente et byggeprosjekt p\u00e5 fjellheisplat\u00e5et under visse betingelser, inkludert en avtale om opparbeiding av utomhusarealer. Etter at anlegget skiftet eierskap, ble det n\u00f8dvendig med noen modifikasjoner i byggeplanene, som ble presentert for kommunen i m\u00f8te. Konklusjonen var at tiltaket m\u00e5 gjennom en detaljregulering for \u00e5 stadfeste etablert arealbruk og legge til rette for nybygg p\u00e5 Fjellstua.\n\nThe outdoor areas around Fjellstua have experienced significant wear and tear due to increased traffic, leading to safety concerns that need to be addressed. There is a desire to accommodate more users through universal design. The proposed plan includes designated building areas for certain properties and recreational areas for others, with boundaries set to only include necessary space for planned activities. The project is prompted by a proposed new building on Fjellstua, which has been in use for 60 years without an established plan.\n\nPlanomr\u00e5det omfatter eiendommene 17/1473 og -1475, avsatt til byggeform\u00e5l og friomr\u00e5der. Planen er avgrenset for \u00e5 sikre arealbruk for gjennomf\u00f8ring av tiltak. Tiltakene inkluderer nytt bygg for \u00f8vre stasjon og Fjellstua, med fokus p\u00e5 universell utforming og adkomst via gondolbanen og Sherpatrappa. Detaljprosjektering vil inkludere tilpasninger for svaksynte og andre tilgjengelighetsfaktorer f\u00f8r det s\u00f8kes om godkjenning.\n\nTechnical design will be carried out in accordance with the disciplines described in the implementation plan. The design will be done in connection with detailed planning and will be responsible in the application for a permit to start construction. The new station at Fjellstua will have a clear identity as an access point to the mountain, with the roof designed to accommodate the building's program while evoking a mountain landscape. The choice of materials will aim to create a sense of being in nature, with surfaces left raw and untreated to showcase the structural elements. The main structure will be a framework in glued laminated timber, with the construction visible in the roof, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere.\n\nThe project of B\u00beringen for glasset will use glued wooden pillars instead of traditional aluminum solutions. Hamran/Johansen Arkitekter AS is responsible for the project, which includes a new building for the upper station and Fjellstua, as well as landscaping around the plateau. The design focuses on universal accessibility, with all public areas on one level linked to the platform by an elevator. Technical planning will involve various fields as outlined in the implementation plan.\n\nProsjekteringen av den nye stasjonen p\u00e5 Fjellstua i Troms\u00f8 vil bli ansvarsbelagt ved s\u00f8knad om igangsettingstillatelse. Bygningen skal ha en klar identitet som adkomst til fjellet, med et funksjonelt tak som gir assosiasjoner til fjellandskapet. Materialvalget skal v\u00e6re r\u00e5 og ubehandlet for \u00e5 harmonisere med naturen, med hovedkonstruksjon i limtre og synlige konstruktive elementer. Glassb\u00e6ringen planlegges \u00e5 v\u00e6re utf\u00f8rt med limtrestolper.\n\nSummary: The new Fjellstua building will be designed to meet current needs and be equipped to meet future needs. It will have a modern and appealing design with a focus on quality and sustainable solutions. The project emphasizes good solutions for the environment, sustainability, and accessibility for all. Measures are being taken to improve safety and minimize damage to the popular Fjellheisplat\u0152et area, ensuring the area can handle a high number of visitors while preserving its natural beauty. Access for people with disabilities is also being considered.\n\nThe goal is to improve accessibility at the site by using robust materials to accommodate a large number of users with diverse needs. Existing elements like the Sherpa stairs, Fjellstua, and Storsteinen will be connected with paved paths. Universal accessibility will be established between Fjellstua and Storsteinen for wheelchair users and visually impaired individuals. The Fjellheisen elevator will provide access to those who can't access the mountain in other ways. Measures will be taken to minimize wear and tear on the natural surroundings due to increased traffic from visitors. Establishing designated paths will help protect the terrain from excessive wear.\n\nThis is a summary of a project by HAMRAN/JOHANSEN ARKITEKTER AS for the construction of a new building at Fjellstua that is modern, high quality, and environmentally sustainable. The project also includes improvements to the outdoor areas at the Fjellheisplat\u00e5et in Troms\u00f8 to increase safety for visitors and protect the environment, while also making the area more accessible for everyone, including people with disabilities. The project aims to ensure that the natural qualities of the area are preserved and vegetation can recover, while accommodating the high number of visitors to the area.\n\nThe goal is to make the area accessible for a large number of users with varying needs by using robust materials for physical infrastructure. Established paths will connect existing elements like the Sherpa stairs, Fjellstua, and Storsteinen effectively. Universal accessibility will be created between Fjellstua and Storsteinen, making the surfaces suitable for wheelchair users and visually impaired individuals. The area should be developed to benefit as many people as possible, with features like information points and seating areas. The Sherpa stairs and increasing traffic from the Fjellheisen are causing wear and tear on the vegetation and natural surroundings. The development of the outdoor area will minimize damage to the terrain, and visitors are encouraged to use the established path network to avoid further damage.\n\nSkilting og fysiske barrierer skal hindre folk fra \u00e5 g\u00e5 utenfor opparbeidede gangveier og stier p\u00e5 Fjellheisplat\u00e5et i Troms\u00f8. Dette tiltaket er ment \u00e5 forbedre sikkerheten og opplevelsen for b\u00e5de tilreisende og lokale bes\u00f8kende, og s\u00f8rge for at omr\u00e5det forblir attraktivt i fremtiden.\n\nThe Fjellheis plateau in Troms\u00f8 is the city's most important tourist attraction and has seen a significant increase in visitors in recent years. Safety measures are being implemented to prevent accidents in areas with steep drops. The development project by Hamran/Johansen Architects aims to create a visually striking building that also blends well with the surrounding landscape.\n\nThe existing building has a total floor area of 609m2, while the planned new building has a total floor area of 2013m2. The planned building will have two floors above ground level, which is an increase of one floor from the current building. The maximum height is C+430.2M. The existing building is old and has undergone changes without an overall plan, resulting in a building that is not aesthetically pleasing, functional, or universally designed. The new building aims to improve aesthetics, accommodate universal design, and meet energy requirements. The outdoor area will also be redesigned to enhance universal design, improve safety, and preserve vegetation and landscape. The new station at the mountain entrance will be designed to blend in with the surrounding landscape and evoke a sense of being in nature.\n\nThis text discusses the importance of natural and untreated surfaces, as well as the planned measures to protect and repair vulnerable ground vegetation in outdoor areas. The design aims to limit traffic to pathways to minimize damage to the ground. The architecture firm HAMRAN/JOHANSEN ARKITEKTER AS emphasizes the visibility and integration of the building into the landscape, while also being a prominent structure in the city. The planned new building will have a total floor area of 2013m2 with two floors above ground level, which is an increase from the current building's 609m2 floor area.\n\nDen eksisterende bebyggelsen er gammel og mangler en overordnet plan, noe som har resultert i lite hensiktsmessige bygninger. Det nye bygget vil fokusere p\u00e5 estetikk, universell utforming og energikrav. Utomhusanlegget vil legge til rette for universell utforming og vern av vegetasjonen. Bygget vil tilpasses landskapet rundt, med et tak som assosierer til fjellandskap og materialer som passer inn i naturen. Utomhusarealene vil ogs\u00e5 fokusere p\u00e5 \u00e5 sk\u00e5ne og reparere s\u00e5rbare bunnvegetasjonen.\n\nAll traffic is planned to be directed towards walkways to minimize damage to the ground. The design of the walkways follows the natural topography to minimize disturbance to the terrain. The property is unregulated and the building area is designated in the municipality's zoning plan for necessary agricultural and reindeer husbandry activities based on the farm's resources. Parts of the area are in a risk zone for landslides and avalanches. There are no ongoing plans in the area.\n\nThe document outlines the key interests affected by the proposed project, including outdoor recreational interests and visual qualities of the building. It also addresses how societal security will be ensured through risk prevention and vulnerability mitigation measures. The plan will undergo a safety analysis with a focus on various factors such as natural hazards and biodiversity. Relevant public authorities and interested parties will be notified about the project initiation, and so far, no objections have been raised by the relevant sector authorities.\n\nThis document outlines the processes for collaboration and participation from relevant authorities, landowners, tenants, neighbors, and other affected parties in planning matters. It emphasizes that participation in planning cases is a minimum requirement under the Planning and Building Act, but additional participation may be necessary in some cases. It also highlights the significant interests affected by the planning initiative, such as outdoor interests and visual qualities of the building. The document also states that measures for community safety, including risk prevention and vulnerability prevention, will be ensured through a risk and vulnerability analysis.\n\nSummary:\nSection 4-3 of the plan focuses on race, flood and landslide risk, ground conditions - geotechnics, wind assessment, biodiversity, VAO framework plan and OSG framework plan. Public authorities and stakeholders such as the State Administration, County Municipality, Sami Parliament, Avinor, and Tromsdalen District Council have been informed about the project. Collaboration and participation from relevant authorities, landowners, tenants, neighbors, and other stakeholders will follow the requirements of the Planning and Building Act. The project is considered to be of particular importance and a neighborhood meeting will be held to present the plans and discuss further participation processes. The project falls under the Environmental Impact Assessment Regulation Annex II.\n\nThe document discusses a proposed development project for a ski resort, including hoppers, ski lifts, and associated facilities. The project aims to improve social, environmental, and economic sustainability. The existing infrastructure is outdated and inefficient, and the new development plans to use sustainable building methods to minimize environmental impact. The project also aims to improve accessibility for all visitors, including those with disabilities. The document also outlines the economic benefits of the project, such as increased tourism, job creation, and local economic growth. The architects request input from stakeholders and plan to address various regulatory and planning considerations in upcoming meetings.Marijne Janssens from Arkitektkontoret Amundsen AS is requesting written confirmation regarding the legal binding of the planned building outline for the upper station of the Fjellheisen project. She wants to ensure that the upper station must be built within the outlined area (+/- 2.0m) and not according to the regulated building boundary/contour line. She also requested a DWG format of the plankartet for reference.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r responds to Lars Hamran's question about the scale of the outdoor space plan for the Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon, confirming that the agreed scale is 1:500 but suggesting also including a 1:1000 scale for better overview if necessary. She also discusses the need for an OSG plan in the project, indicating that it will overlap with the proposed plan and can be integrated into the plan's impact assessment chapter. She advises contacting Tobias H\u00fcbscher for guidance on developing the OSG plan and signs off with her contact information.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r is working on implementing a shuttle bus service from the city center to Fjellheisen's lower station. The service will operate during the summer and winter seasons to address overcrowding issues at bus stops such as \"Fjellheisen\". Ulf Johansen, the manager of Fjellheisen, confirms plans to restart the shuttle service and acknowledges the need for better marketing. Communication between Margareth and Ulf indicates a discussion about the shuttle bus service and its availability during the peak season. Additionally, Margareth has been dealing with comments from the county municipality regarding the impact of plan 1956 Fjellheisen upper station on public transportation and the need for mitigating measures in the plan documentation. Roger Fagerheim, the CEO of Frabene AS, expresses anticipation for feedback from the authorities regarding the plan.Marijne Janssens from Arkitektkontoret Amundsen AS is seeking clarification on the binding nature of the planned building outline shown on the plankart for Plan 1956 Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon. Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an area planner from Troms\u00f8 kommune, explains that the planned building outline is legally binding with a margin of +/- 2 meters, except towards the east where it coincides with the building boundary. The regulated height curve is also outlined in the plan, with the maximum height for the new mountain lodge set at kote +433. Sundf\u00f8r clarifies that if the location of the planned building is adjusted within the margin, the regulated height curve will also adjust accordingly. Janssens had previously requested the plankart in dwg format and sought confirmation that the planned building outline is legally binding.Lars Hamran, an architect, is concerned that the developer may be burdened with additional responsibilities as a result of a new building regulation process. He believes that the terms of the agreement between the developer and the Park, Sports, and Recreation department should be upheld and referenced in the planning initiative. Katarzyna Maria Fitz, a landscape architect from the municipality, disagrees, stating that no such agreement has been finalized and that it is not appropriate to enter into such an agreement during the planning process. The municipality recommends that minor adjustments be made to the planning initiative to avoid implying that such an agreement is in place or will be entered into.Norges Handikapforbund i Troms\u00f8 er forn\u00f8yde med \u00e5 v\u00e6re involvert tidlig i planprosessen for nybygg til Fjellstua og utomhusomr\u00e5der. De \u00f8nsker \u00e5 sikre universelt utformede l\u00f8sninger og har noen kommentarer til planbeskrivelsen. De presiserer behovet for universell tilgjengelighet og kvalitetsstandarder for utend\u00f8rsomr\u00e5der, og \u00f8nsker at disse kommentarene blir innarbeidet i plandokumentet. Kontaktperson er Geirmund Dalen, lokallagsleder i Norges Handikapforbund Troms\u00f8.Lars Hamran sent a revised draft of plan specifications for the Fjellheisen upper station to Margareth Sundf\u00f8r and Erik Eidesen for their meeting on March 28. Margareth provided feedback, noting some missing elements and suggesting the meeting would be a working session. She also mentioned the possibility of combining the plan proposal and building permit review. Lars previously forwarded the draft to Margareth and requested feedback before the meeting.Lars has sent Margareth revised regulations in response to her comments. He has made some changes and additions, and suggests discussing certain regulations before their meeting on Thursday. He encourages Margareth to call if she needs clarification.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an area planner at Troms\u00f8 kommune, has granted an extension for the submission of an opinion on plan 1956 Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon to the Statsforvalteren until January 18, 2024. Gaute Sletteland from Statsforvalteren had requested the extension via phone call and email earlier that day. The original request for an extension was sent by Margareth Wegner Sundfoer.Dokumentet er en uttalelse fra Statens vegvesen ang\u00e5ende en plan for detaljregulering for Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon i Troms\u00f8 kommune. Planen g\u00e5r ut p\u00e5 \u00e5 bygge en ny fjellstue med taubanestasjon og tiltak i offentlig friomr\u00e5de. Statens vegvesen uttaler seg som ansvarlig for \u00e5 ivareta nasjonale retningslinjer for transportplanlegging, og p\u00e5peker at planen b\u00f8r inkludere forbedringer ved nedre stasjon.utenom dette har de ingen merknader.Lars and Margareth are discussing the need for regulations regarding downward lighting at Fjellheisen. Margareth believes it is important to include such regulations not only for aviation safety but also to reduce light pollution and positively impact public health. She also mentions a legal document on light pollution that could be helpful. Lars agrees that these regulations are important and will look into the provided link.Lars Hamran is questioning a decision that prohibits snow removal with machines in a specific area. He believes it may be impractical and not necessary to regulate under the planning and building laws. He suggests removing this restriction.Skred AS har gitt skredfaglige innspill til en ROS-analyse for Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon. Notatet oppsummerer vurderingene og innspillene som ble gitt av Skred AS i forbindelse med deres detaljprosjektering av skredsikring for ny bunnstasjon p\u00e5 vegne av Fjellheisen AS. Bakgrunnen for innspillene var at planomr\u00e5det ikke l\u00e5 innenfor NVE sine aktsomhetssoner for skred, men utl\u00f8sningsomr\u00e5der og utl\u00f8psomr\u00e5der i aktsomhetskartene l\u00e5 like nedenfor.\n\nMulticonsult assessed the risk of rockfall, mudslides, loose mass, and rockslides as too high, and recommended a detailed avalanche risk assessment to clarify the actual avalanche risk in relation to the planning area. Skred AS received comments regarding the different avalanche processes with increased risk and stated that further evaluation was needed. Skred AS pointed out that the planning area is located outside the caution areas in NVE's caution map for landslides and floods and highlighted the potential triggering factors for avalanches such as increased rainfall and climate conditions. They recommended that risk assessments for avalanches and ground conditions should be conducted by geotechnical experts due to high uncertainty, and the risk and vulnerability assessment for the planning area cannot be excluded.\n\nSummary: A general assessment is made for this and related topics in Chapter 5.1.1. It is emphasized that there is a need for better data and assessments conducted by a geotechnical engineer or equivalent expert to adequately assess the risk of rockfall and mudslides in the planning area. Without such evaluations, it cannot be determined if these factors pose a risk. The risk of landslides/ground conditions should be assessed by a geotechnical engineer or equivalent expert due to high uncertainty. In regards to mudslides, they are most likely to occur during periods of heavy rain or rapid snowmelt, and typically in areas with at least 0.5m of snow depth. The area where the planning site is located has 50-200 cm of snow depth and steep slopes, making it susceptible to mudslides.\n\nS\u00f8rpeskred og fjellskred utgj\u00f8r en potensiell fare for stabiliteten i planomr\u00e5det, men det er behov for ytterligere unders\u00f8kelser av geoteknikere eller andre fagkyndige for \u00e5 kunne vurdere risikoen n\u00f8yaktig. Mangel p\u00e5 kartlegging av skredsonen gj\u00f8r det vanskelig \u00e5 fastsl\u00e5 n\u00f8yaktig risikoniv\u00e5. Storsteinen er identifisert som et potensielt ustabilt omr\u00e5de med lav sannsynlighet for fjellskred. Faglig vurdering av skredrisiko og grunnforhold er n\u00f8dvendig for \u00e5 kunne h\u00e5ndtere disse farene p\u00e5 en adekvat m\u00e5te.\n\nDet vises i detaljreguleringsplanen at det er hensynssone for ras- og skredfare i planomr\u00e5det, men skredsonen er ikke kartlagt. Det anbefales at risikovurderinger for skred/grunnforhold utf\u00f8res av geoteknikere eller andre fagkyndige, da usikkerheten rundt dette temaet ikke kan utelukkes. Skredfaren mot toppstasjonen trenger ikke utredes etter TEK17 \u00a77-3, men det bratte terrenget under har aktsomhets- og faresoner for skred. Faresoner for skred i bratt terreng er kartlagt i omr\u00e5det, men ikke trukket opp til toppstasjonen i Troms\u00f8 kommune. Rapporten utf\u00f8rt av NGI i 2016 ligger til grunn for skredsikring av bunnstasjonen til fjellheisen.\n\nThe Storsteinen highlighted has a low probability of loosening, allowing for safety measures to be implemented within the danger zone. The top station for Fjellheisen is not affected by the loosening or release areas. Skog AS has determined that forested areas within the plan area do not significantly impact avalanche risk. Additional avalanche protection measures are planned for the new bottom station. Detailed avalanche risk assessment is not deemed necessary for the new top station due to the absence of loosening areas. Construction safety requirements are ensured through engineering expertise and legal regulations.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an urban planner at Troms\u00f8 municipality, granted an extension for the deadline to provide feedback on plan 1956 Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon until January 15, 2024, in response to a request from Christina Solhaug Joakimsen, a planning advisor at Troms fylkeskommune.Dette er en e-post fra NVE (Norges vassdrags- og energidirektorat) ang\u00e5ende varsel om oppstart av detaljregulering for Fjellheisen i Troms\u00f8 kommune. NVE gir generell informasjon om deres ansvarsomr\u00e5der og veiledning for hvordan nasjonale og regionale interesser skal ivaretas i reguleringsplaner. De oppfordrer forslagsstillere til \u00e5 bruke deres kartbaserte veileder og internettressurser for arealplanlegging. NVE vil prioritere \u00e5 gi innspill til planer som ber\u00f8rer deres saksomr\u00e5der og krever at relevant dokumentasjon og fagutredninger blir vedlagt planer sendt til dem for h\u00f8ring. Det oppfordres til \u00e5 ta kontakt med NVE for konkret bistand ved behov.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r sent an email to Roger Fagerheim and Andre Severin Johansen with the subject \"stasjon\" attaching the meeting minutes and presentation from the meeting held on October 13, 2023 regarding plan 1956 for Fjellheisen \u00f8vre. Sundf\u00f8r, an area planner at Troms\u00f8 kommune, signed off the email with her contact information and a disclaimer regarding the handling of emails sent to Troms\u00f8 kommune.This document outlines the timeline and process for the development and approval of a plan for the UTKAST-Fremdri.splan Fjellheisen \u00d8vre stasjon in 1956. The document includes various steps such as preparing the plan, holding meetings with stakeholders, submitting the proposal to the municipality, and undergoing public review and approval. The process also includes specific deadlines and milestones to be met throughout the planning process.Bes\u00f8ksadresse: R\u00e5dhusgata 2, 9008 Troms\u00f8, Postadresse: Postboks 6900 Langnes, 9299 Troms\u00f8, Telefon: 77 79 00 00, E-post: postmottak@tromso.kommune.no, Org.nr.: Foretaksregisteret NO 940 101 808 MVA tromso.kommune.no. HAMRAN/JOHANSEN ARKITEKTER AS Skur 35Akershusstranda 15 0150 OSLO. M\u00f8tesammendrag fra SAMORG-m\u00f8tet om planinitiativ for detaljregulering for Fjellstua \u00f8vre stasjon. Fagenhetene i kommunen har gitt innspill som kan p\u00e5virke framtidige f\u00f8ringer. Nesten alle merknadene er i stikkordsform og trenger muligens ytterligere klargj\u00f8ring. Byplan v/arkitektur \u00f8nsker et signalbygg med store glassfasader, men samtidig vektlegges naturopplevelser som nordlys.\n\nKunstig lys b\u00f8r ikke skade omgivelsene, og det er behov for avklaring om hvordan man skal ta hensyn til dette. Det reises sp\u00f8rsm\u00e5l om en takterrasse om vinteren er en god id\u00e9, spesielt med tanke p\u00e5 om det vil passe inn i naturen. Det diskuteres om en konstruert terrasse er n\u00f8dvendig, da den n\u00e5v\u00e6rende terrassen fungerer godt for alle aldersgrupper. Bygningsvolumet m\u00e5 vurderes i forhold til landskapet for \u00e5 sikre \"reelle opplevelser\" for brukerne. Det positivt til tiltak for universell utforming og sp\u00f8rsm\u00e5l om vinterdrift av uteomr\u00e5det. Det b\u00f8r vurderes om maskinbr\u00f8ytede stier er riktig i stedet for tr\u00e5kkede stier, og materialbruken m\u00e5 tilpasses omgivelsene for \u00e5 unng\u00e5 unaturlige l\u00f8sninger som glassrekkeverk.\n\nOppsummering:\nEt planinitiativ for detaljregulering av Fjellstua \u00f8vre stasjon ble presentert i et kommunalt samordningsm\u00f8te. Det er \u00f8nske om et \"signalbygg\" med store glassfasader, men samtidig vektlegges naturopplevelser som nordlys. ARK gruppa mener at natur/landskap b\u00f8r v\u00e6re den prim\u00e6re opplevelsen, og at bygningen b\u00f8r underordnes dette. Kunstig lys b\u00f8r ikke \u00f8delegge omgivelsene. Det har v\u00e6rt en gjennomgang av merknader fra ulike fagenheter i kommunen, som kan gi f\u00f8ringer for oppstartsm\u00f8tet. Rekkverk i tilknytning til takterrasse vil fastlegge bygningen mer i Troms\u00f8 kommune.\n\nVurdering av hvordan takterrasse og bygningsvolum b\u00f8r tilpasses til omgivelsene. Diskusjon om behovet for en ny terrassel\u00f8sning og om den foresl\u00e5tte konstruksjonen er n\u00f8dvendig. Fokus p\u00e5 tilgjengelighet for alle og behovet for \u00e5 opprettholde dagens terrassel\u00f8sning mot vestbyen. Sp\u00f8rsm\u00e5l knyttet til vinterdrift av uteareal og materialvalg for stier og rekkverk for \u00e5 tilpasse seg omgivelsene.\n\nThe building is now open in all directions, including from the roof, is this correct - light exposure? The proposed glass roof setup facing the city may be too much. The proposed railing for the rooftop terrace will determine the building height, which cannot be approved. There is a question about the necessity of the rooftop terrace as shown. If allowed, the area should be reduced to ensure the railing is not visible from the main building line.\n\nThe outdoor area on the ground level should be closer to the building to create natural seating areas protected from wind for people/walkers. Currently, all seating on the east side is in exposed areas. There must also be seating along the building for safety.\n\nThe terrace above the elevator house should be for the public to enjoy the view and have their meals. It is important that the mountain lift is seen as a public place accessible to all.\n\nDet er positivt at det vil v\u00e6re toalettfasiliteter med tilgang utend\u00f8rs, men etablering av kunstig lekeplass oppfattes negativt da naturen allerede er en lekeplass. Materialbruk b\u00f8r vurderes med tanke p\u00e5 hva som finnes i naturen, og alternativ l\u00f8sninger b\u00f8r vurderes. Det burde v\u00e6rt krav om en arkitektkonkurranse for \u00e5 se alternative l\u00f8sninger. Krav om bygningsvolum, estetikk og materialbruk m\u00e5 avklares i planprosessen. Det b\u00f8r ogs\u00e5 vurderes om prosjektet er sosialt b\u00e6rekraftig og til nytte for lokalbefolkningen. Uteomr\u00e5det b\u00f8r inkludere b\u00e5lplasser og estetikken ved nedre stasjon m\u00e5 ogs\u00e5 tas i betraktning. Tiltaket vil sannsynligvis \u00f8ke trafikken og det kan skape utfordringer p\u00e5 Anton Jakobsen veg som mangler fortau p\u00e5 store deler av strekningen.\n\nDet vurderes om veg og fortau langs Anton Jakobsen veg b\u00f8r inkluderes i reguleringsplanen, samt rekkef\u00f8lgekrav. En trafikkanalyse b\u00f8r gjennomf\u00f8res for omr\u00e5det ved nedre stasjon/startpunktet for stier for \u00e5 identifisere anbefalte tiltak p\u00e5 grunn av lav standard p\u00e5 b\u00e5de veg og gatenett. Universell utforming av gangbanen b\u00f8r sikres med belysning og eventuelt h\u00e5ndl\u00f8per, uten \u00e5 for\u00e5rsake lysforurensning. Gjerder og andre sikkerhetstiltak b\u00f8r vurderes for \u00e5 ivareta tryggheten til adkomstomr\u00e5dene. Utbygger m\u00e5 inng\u00e5 avtale med grunneierne for bruk av grunn. Illustrasjonstegninger m\u00e5 v\u00e6re detaljerte og m\u00e5lsatte for \u00e5 v\u00e6re juridisk bindende. Det b\u00f8r vurderes \u00e5 legge til gjerder eller sikkerhetstiltak ved den underjordiske delen av bygget for \u00e5 sikre trygg adgang.\n\nThe fence may have an impact on the building's visual expression and there is ambiguity regarding the purpose of the door in this part of the building. It is questioned whether people are intended to use this route to the gondolas, and if so, provisions for heavy pedestrian traffic need to be made without affecting the building's height. It is also questioned whether the rooftop terrace is necessary, and if allowed, the area may need to be reduced to ensure that the railing is not visible from the roofline. Outdoor areas on the ground level should be closer to the building to create natural sun and wind-protected seating areas. It is important to ensure that the terrace above the elevator house is accessible to the public for enjoying views and picnic meals. The establishment of an artificial playground is viewed negatively, as the natural environment should be utilized for recreational purposes.\n\nI planlegging av lekeplass b\u00f8r materialbruk vurderes med tanke p\u00e5 \u00e5 bruke naturlige materialer og unng\u00e5 impregnert treverk, plast og gummi. Det b\u00f8r ogs\u00e5 v\u00e6re alternative l\u00f8sninger og arkitektkonkurranse for \u00e5 se ulike designmuligheter. Bygningsvolum, h\u00f8yder, materialbruk og estetikk m\u00e5 avklares i planprosessen, og det b\u00f8r ogs\u00e5 tas hensyn til sosial b\u00e6rekraft og om prosjektet kommer lokalbefolkningen til gode. Videre b\u00f8r det vurderes b\u00e5lplasser ute og estetikk/sammensetning nedre stasjon. Tiltaket vil mest sannsynlig \u00f8ke trafikken, og det b\u00f8r vurderes om veg og fortau langs Anton Jakobsen veg skal inkluderes i reguleringsplan og eventuelle rekkef\u00f8lgekrav.\n\nDet b\u00f8r ideelt sett gjennomf\u00f8res en trafikkanalyse for omr\u00e5det ved nedre stasjon/startpunkt for stier for \u00e5 anbefale tiltak. Standarden p\u00e5 vei og gatenett er generelt lav for alle trafikantgrupper. For universell utforming av gangbanen m\u00e5 den v\u00e6re belyst, men lysforurensningen b\u00f8r minimeres. Eiendomsforhold m\u00e5 avklares med grunneierne, og illustrasjonstegninger m\u00e5 v\u00e6re korrekte og m\u00e5lsatte hvis de skal v\u00e6re juridisk bindende. Gjerder b\u00f8r vurderes n\u00f8ye for \u00e5 sikre trygghet og estetikk. En underjordisk del av bygget mangler gjerde til stien ned dit og det b\u00f8r vurderes n\u00f8ye med tanke p\u00e5 sikkerhet og visuelt uttrykk.\n\nDet m\u00e5 avklares om personer skal benytte veien til gondolene, og det b\u00f8r legges til rette for mye persontrafikk i planprosessen. H\u00f8yden p\u00e5 gjerder p\u00e5 takterrassen m\u00e5 vurderes for \u00e5 ivareta sikkerheten, samt behovet for varmeelementer om vinteren. Det er ikke aktuelt \u00e5 gi midlertidig dispensasjon f\u00f8r et komplett planforslag er sendt p\u00e5 h\u00f8ring i minst 6 uker. Dispensasjonss\u00f8knader vil bli vurdert etter dette tidspunktet.\n\nVi kan ikke konkludere med en beslutning f\u00f8r vi har mottatt en begrunnet s\u00f8knad og sett eventuelle svar og innsigelser til planforslaget. Sikringsgjerdet og sherpatrappen mot Storsteinen er s\u00f8knadspliktige og m\u00e5 f\u00f8lge bestemte retningslinjer for utforming og h\u00f8yde. Det er viktig \u00e5 ha en bestemmelse i planen om gjerdets utforming for \u00e5 sikre forutsigbarhet og muligheten for byggesaksbehandling. Lyngen kommune har s\u00f8kt om tillatelse til oppf\u00f8ring av sherpatrapp og dispensasjon fra LNFR-reglene.\n\nStatsforvalteren opphevet et vedtak i januar 2022 fordi de mente tiltaket ikke var tilstrekkelig opplyst og at det ikke var tatt stilling til om det utl\u00f8ste krav om reguleringsplan. Samme problemstilling vil kunne oppst\u00e5 i dette tilfellet. Det kreves en forenklet VAO-rammeplan for vann og avl\u00f8p, og det er behov for tydelig design og skilting for \u00e5 sikre at utomhusanlegget er tilgjengelig for allmennheten. Det er ogs\u00e5 viktig \u00e5 ta hensyn til botaniske verdier og vegetasjon for \u00e5 unng\u00e5 slitasje. Byggesakene m\u00e5 f\u00f8lge plan- og bygningsloven, og det er viktig \u00e5 vurdere virkningen av tiltak sett fra KULA-omr\u00e5det. Fokus b\u00f8r ogs\u00e5 v\u00e6re p\u00e5 \u00e5 minimere lysforurensing og naturinngrep.\u00f8nsker fortsatt avklaring p\u00e5 en del ting.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r sent an email to attendees of a meeting about the detailed regulation of the Fjellheisen upper station on September 21, 2022. She attached a draft of the meeting minutes and the presentation. She requested feedback on the minutes by September 27 and asked recipients to confirm their contact information and representation in the document. She also mentioned that all emails to Troms\u00f8 municipality are subject to public disclosure.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r is inquiring about which document serves as the concept sketch for the collaborative project specified in the plan description and regulations. Lars confirms that the forprosjektet in vedlegg 14 (also called illustrasjonsprosjekt utomhus) is the concept sketch for the collaboration project. This email exchange is related to Plan 1956 Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r apologizes for the delay in responding to Heidi Halmstr\u00f8m's email regarding attachments to proposal 1956 for the upper station of Fjellheisen. She provides a link to where all the attachments can be found and explains that the email was only brought to her attention on December 8. Sundf\u00f8r signs off as an urban planner in the Section for Urban Development at Troms\u00f8 Municipality.An invitation has been sent for a neighborhood meeting regarding the development of detailed regulations for the upper station of Fjellheisen. The meeting aims to inform neighbors about the local situation, encourage participation in the planning process, and provide information about submitting feedback. The meeting will include a presentation of the plans by the municipality and Hamran/Johansen Architects AS.The email is forwarding a revised Risk and Vulnerability Assessment (ROSF) report for the Fjellheisen project, which has been updated based on new information from a geologist. The sender mentions that they have not had time to internally review the report due to a colleague being on sick leave, but will provide feedback if they disagree with anything in the report. The email also includes contact information for further correspondence.A meeting was held on March 28, 2023 regarding the plan for the upper station of Fjellheisen. The meeting discussed the progress of the plan, consultation with reindeer herding districts, collaboration with the municipality, and feedback on draft plan provisions and maps. Issues such as the need for a temporary construction road, conditions for outdoor area activities, and the possibility of an OSG plan were also discussed. The meeting concluded with further clarification on the establishment of a temporary construction road and the importance of adhering to regulations.The document contains an agenda for a meeting regarding the start of a new regulatory plan for the upper station of Fjellheisen. It outlines the topics to be discussed, including the municipality's planning parameters, consultation with Sami law, and the process and timeline for the plan. The meeting is scheduled for December 8, 2022, and stakeholders are encouraged to submit a proposal for the plan's timeline before the meeting. The document also includes contact information for the relevant parties.Hamran/Johansen Arkitekter AS har utarbeidet en planbeskrivelse for Fjellheisen Troms\u00f8 p\u00e5 vegne av tiltakshaver Fjellheisen AS. Planen omhandler detaljregulering for den \u00f8vre stasjonen av fjellheisen i Troms\u00f8 kommune. Bakgrunnen for planen, planprosessen, planstatus og rammebetingelser, samt beskrivelse av planomr\u00e5det og eksisterende forhold er inkludert i dokumentet. Det tas hensyn til faktorer som landskap, kulturminner, naturverdier, trafikk, folkehelse, og teknisk infrastruktur i planleggingen av prosjektet.\n\nThis is a description of a mountain lift project in Troms\u00f8, including information about ground conditions, noise levels, air pollution, existing risks and vulnerabilities, land use plans, building placement and design, parking, infrastructure connections, traffic and transportation, environmental monitoring, accessibility, cultural heritage, social infrastructure, water and waste management plans.\n\nThe document outlines various solutions and measures to mitigate risks in the Fjellheisen Troms\u00f8 plan. It includes aspects such as order regulations, impact assessment, consequences of the plan proposal, landscape, cultural heritage, traffic and transportation, energy and climate, economic implications, and stakeholder interests. It also discusses the implementation of the plan, including transportation of construction materials, planned timeline, and compliance with sector regulations.\n\nFjellheisen AS, med Hamran/Johansen Arkitekter som plankonsulent, \u00f8nsker \u00e5 utarbeide en detaljreguleringsplan for Fjellheisplat\u00e5et i Troms\u00f8. Planen inkluderer et nytt bygg for \u00f8vre stasjon og Fjellstua, samt opparbeiding av utomhusomr\u00e5det rundt plat\u00e5et. M\u00e5let er \u00e5 etablere et framtidsrettet og b\u00e6rekraftig nybygg, samtidig som man \u00f8nsker \u00e5 forbedre fysisk tilrettelegging, minimere slitasje p\u00e5 terrenget og sikre omr\u00e5der med fare for fallulykker. Prosjektet vektlegger milj\u00f8vennlige l\u00f8sninger og tilgjengelighet for alle brukere. Opparbeidede stier binder eksisterende elementer sammen og tar vare p\u00e5 naturen og vegetasjonen p\u00e5 plat\u00e5et.\n\nHensikten med planen er \u00e5 stadfeste etablert arealbruk p\u00e5 \u00f8vre stasjon og Fjellstua, samt \u00e5 legge til rette for nybygg. Det legges opp til \u00f8kt aktivitet gjennom hele \u00e5ret, b\u00e5de sommer og vinter, med sikte p\u00e5 \u00e5 tilrettelegge for hel\u00e5rsturisme og rekreasjon for ulike brukere. Omr\u00e5det har v\u00e6rt i bruk i 60 \u00e5r, men detaljregulering er n\u00f8dvendig p\u00e5 grunn av forslag til nybygg p\u00e5 Fjellstua og \u00f8kt trafikk p\u00e5 fjellheisen. Det er ogs\u00e5 behov for \u00e5 ivareta sikkerhet og universell utforming for flere brukere.\n\nSummary: The plan proposal is for the development of tourism and hospitality facilities on the Fjellheisplat\u00e5et area in Tromsdalen, with a total area of approximately 80 daa. The proposal is submitted by Fjellheisen AS with key landowners including Fjellheisen AS, Troms\u00f8 Kommune, Fl\u00f8yfjellet AS, and Elin L\u00f8vland Fjell, Lars Hagerup, Marianne Ingen L\u00f8vland, Tone Pettersen. The plan is currently unregulated and the main issues being considered include land use, biodiversity, and avalanche risks. The proposal is currently in the initial stages of planning, with a public notice of the start date and the submission of the full plan proposal. A previous application for building permits with dispensation from agricultural and natural area purposes was submitted in October 2020.\n\nTroms\u00f8 kommune godkjente tiltaket ved Fjellheisen med dispensasjon under forutsetning av en avtale mellom tiltakshaver og kommunen om prosjektering og opparbeidelse av utomhusarealer p\u00e5 Fjellheisplat\u00e5et. Etter endringer i byggeplanene ble det konkludert at tiltaket m\u00e5 gjennom en detaljregulering. Kommunen ga rammetillatelse for ombygging av Fjellheisen nedre stasjon i april 2020, men igangsetting av tiltaket er betinget av ferdig prosjektert og godkjent skredsikring. Da eksisterende bebyggelse ble etablert f\u00f8r forskriften om konsekvensutredning tr\u00e5dte i kraft i 2017, er det bare utvidelsen av bygget og tilrettelegging av uteomr\u00e5det som skal vurderes etter forskriften.\n\nPlanarbeidet inneb\u00e6rer ingen endring i bruken eller aktiviteten p\u00e5 Fjellheisplat\u00e5et, men vil kunne tiltrekke flere bes\u00f8kende gjennom bedre tilrettelegging for hel\u00e5rsbruk. St\u00f8y fra helikopterbruk vil begrenses til anleggsperioden. Siden omr\u00e5det er viktig for friluftslivet, kan det utl\u00f8se krav om konsekvensutredning, selv om planen ikke forventes \u00e5 ha vesentlige virkninger p\u00e5 milj\u00f8 eller samfunn. Medvirkningsprosessen har blitt fulgt i henhold til plan- og bygningsloven, med spesiell hensyn til Mauken/Tromsdalen reinbeitedistriktets rett til konsultasjon.\n\nI 2023 er det en frist for tilbakemelding om planbeskrivelsen for Fjellheisen Troms\u00f8 til 25.02.2023. Et naboskapsm\u00f8te ble avholdt i oktober 2022 hvor planene ble presentert. Planen er av s\u00e6rskilt viktighet og grunneiere og sektormyndigheter er varslet om planoppstart. Planen tar hensyn til statlige planretningslinjer og overordnede planer som omr\u00e5dets avsatt areal i kommuneplanen. Det er ingen gjeldende reguleringsplaner i omr\u00e5det da eiendommen er uregulert.\n\nThere are no adjacent plans to the Fjellheisen project. The closest regulated plans are for the Fjellheisen lower station and the Turistvegen-Hungeren area. The project area is also designated as reindeer grazing land and is within a snow and rockslide risk zone. The project site is located at an elevation of 421 meters, with the lower station on Troms\u00f8 mainland 50 meters above sea level.\n\nPlanbeskrivelsen for Fjellheisen Troms\u00f8 viser at omr\u00e5det omfatter en gondolbane og restaurantbygning, som er et popul\u00e6rt utfartssted med 300 000-400 000 bes\u00f8kende \u00e5rlig. Tiltakene som er gjort for \u00e5 \u00f8ke turisme, som installering av nye gondoler og Sherpatrappa, har f\u00f8rt til en stor \u00f8kning i antall bes\u00f8kende og bygget er ikke tilpasset for den \u00f8kte trafikken. Den eksisterende fjellstuen ble bygget i 1992 og ble fornyet i 2016. Landskapet omkring omr\u00e5det er typisk for kystn\u00e6re omr\u00e5der i regionen.\n\nThe landscape of Terrenget features Paleike mountain formations with steep slopes and rounded peaks. The area is open and varied, following the terrain and elevation, with the mountain lift as a visible contrast. There are good sun conditions throughout the day with no shading from surrounding landscapes or vegetation. The local climate in Troms\u00f8 shows the wind rose pattern from 2013 to 2023.\n\nThe text discusses wind conditions in Troms\u00f8, with specific wind speeds categorized from calm to hurricane force. A wind rose diagram is provided as a reference for assessing wind risks and vulnerabilities in the area. Additionally, the area is noted for its aesthetic and cultural value, being part of a cultural heritage landscape of national interest. The plan area is on the outskirts of the cultural heritage area, with the cable car being an important building for Troms\u00f8 and its identity.\n\nDet er viktig \u00e5 vurdere tilpasningen av tiltaket til omgivelsene, inkludert fjernvirkning. Belysning og lysforurensning knyttet til bygg og uteromsarealer m\u00e5 ogs\u00e5 vurderes. Planomr\u00e5det ble NIN-kartlagt i 2021 med forskjellig kvalitet p\u00e5 naturtyper. Fl\u00f8ya er en viktig naturtypelokalitet. Fjellheisplat\u00e5et er et knutepunkt for popul\u00e6re turstier, inkludert Sherpatrappa.\n\nThe Fl\u00f8ya mountain in Troms\u00f8 has several possible starting points, including the Sherpa steps in the north and the Dalberg path in the south. The path leads to the Steinb\u00f8hytta stone cabin, restored by Troms Turlag. The Fjellheisen Troms\u00f8 plan includes enhancing the plateau for year-round use, with access via gondola or on foot, especially from the Sherpa steps. Improved traffic and parking at the lower station are key goals for Fjellheisen AS and Troms\u00f8 municipality.\n\nI planprosessen for \u00f8vre stasjon har kommunen erkjent at utfordringene ikke vil bli l\u00f8st gjennom detaljreguleringen, men i andre prosesser senere. Folkehelseunders\u00f8kelsen i Troms og Finnmark fra 2019 viser at tilgang til natur- og friluftsomr\u00e5der, trivsel i n\u00e6rmilj\u00f8et og antall timer stillesitting er relevante temaer for planomr\u00e5det, og tiltaket kan bidra til \u00e5 forbedre disse. Data viser at Troms\u00f8-omr\u00e5det har lavere tilgang til natur- og friluftsomr\u00e5der, men ligger over gjennomsnittet n\u00e5r det gjelder trivsel i n\u00e6rmilj\u00f8et og antall timer stillesitting.\n\nThe figure shows the average amount of sitting hours per day in Troms and Finnmark regions, with slightly more sitting time in the Troms\u00f8 area compared to the overall average. In terms of planning for children and young people's interests, considerations include outdoor areas, play areas, lighting, sun exposure, green spaces, and access to paths. Fjellstua is the only built-up area in the plan area, offering activities such as a restaurant and souvenir shop. The area around Fjellstua provides ample outdoor space and access to green areas and trails for children and young people.\n\nI 2016 ble anlegget fornyet med nye gondoler og maskineri, samt en forlenget panorama-terrasse og en ny rullestolheis. En av gondolene er rullestolvennlig, og det er en personheis som tar deg til utsiktsplat\u00e5et og Fjellstua. Du kan ta med barnevogn i gondolene, men det er ikke mulig \u00e5 man\u00f8vrere vognen rundt i fjellet. Det er ikke offentlig vann- og avl\u00f8psanlegg innenfor planomr\u00e5det, kun privat til bruk for Fjellstua. Eksisterende VA-anlegg er basert p\u00e5 informasjon fra Troms\u00f8 kommune og driftsansvarlig i Fjellheisen AS.\n\nTanken i forankringsrommet p\u00e5 Fjellstua har et volum p\u00e5 ca. 35 m3 og pumpes vannet til forbruk. Ved str\u00f8mbrudd tilkobles et aggregat for \u00e5 opprettholde trykket. Spillvann pumpes fra Fjellstua til en kommunal avl\u00f8psledning. Overvann h\u00e5ndteres p\u00e5 overflaten og ikke f\u00f8rt til offentlig overvannssystem. Energiforsyningen er prim\u00e6rt basert p\u00e5 el-kraft, men bergvarme kan ogs\u00e5 vurderes som et alternativ.\n\nPlanomr\u00e5det best\u00e5r hovedsakelig av bart fjell med stedvis tynt l\u00f8smassedekke, og det er fare for skred p\u00e5 grunn av \u00f8kt nedb\u00f8r og flomhendelser. Tiltakshaver m\u00e5 dokumentere avstand til elektromagnetiske felt ved planlegging av bebyggelse i n\u00e6rheten av h\u00f8yspentledninger. Det er ingen utbygde nettanlegg innenfor planomr\u00e5det, men en sentralnettlinje g\u00e5r gjennom omr\u00e5det med to master innenfor grenseverdiene for str\u00e5lingssikkerhet. Master, stolper, transformatorstasjoner og sj\u00f8kabler er ogs\u00e5 til stede p\u00e5 planomr\u00e5det.\n\nDeler av planomr\u00e5det ligger innenfor hensynssone for ras- og skredfare, men ellers er det utenfor fare- og aktsomhetssoner i NVEs temakart. Tiltak for skredsikring er satt opp i forbindelse med utbygging av nedre stasjon for fjellheisen. Planomr\u00e5det er isolert fra annen bebyggelse, s\u00e5 st\u00f8y fra bes\u00f8kende er den eneste potensielle st\u00f8ykilden. St\u00f8y fra kraftledninger, som kan oppst\u00e5 som koronast\u00f8y, anses ikke som en betydelig faktor ved fjellheisen i Troms\u00f8.\n\nThe noise map from the KPA shows zones for aircraft and road noise. The air quality in the area is mostly low to moderate, with potential health effects for asthmatics and individuals with respiratory or heart conditions. The project is not expected to significantly increase traffic in the lower station area. A risk and vulnerability analysis by Multiconsult Norge AS for Fjellheisen AS identified 12 relevant risk factors for the area.\n\n. Analyser og utredninger har blitt gjennomf\u00f8rt i forbindelse med planlegging av Fjellheisen Troms\u00f8. Hendelser som skred, vind, taubane ute av drift og vann- og avl\u00f8p er vurdert i en risikomatrise, der vind og skred anses \u00e5 ha h\u00f8y og middels risiko. Bygningstyper i influensomr\u00e5det viser at hotell og resturant utgj\u00f8r majoriteten av bygg. Viktige temaer som barn og unges interesser, universell utforming, folkehelse, trafikk og samferdsel er nevnt i oppstartsm\u00f8tet og blir n\u00f8ye redegjort for i planbeskrivelsen. Andre temaer som naturmangfold, KULA og landskap er ogs\u00e5 grundig utredet som separate vedlegg eller nevnt i planbeskrivelsen.\n\nPlanomr\u00e5det best\u00e5r av 20 eiendommer, inkludert Fjellheisen AS, Troms\u00f8 Kommune, Fl\u00f8yfjellet AS og private eiere. Planen omfatter byggeform\u00e5l p\u00e5 noen eiendommer og friomr\u00e5der p\u00e5 andre. Reguleringsform\u00e5let inkluderer fritids- og turistform\u00e5l, samt friomr\u00e5der. En planavgrensning er foresl\u00e5tt for \u00e5 sikre n\u00f8dvendig arealbruk for gjennomf\u00f8ring av planlagte tiltak.\n\nThis document provides information about various designated areas and purposes in a development plan for Fjellheisen Troms\u00f8. It includes information on areas for buildings and facilities, recreational and tourist purposes, green spaces, agricultural and natural areas, as well as considerations for potential hazards such as landslides and high voltage installations. Specific details are provided for areas such as the Fritids- and turistform\u00e5l (FTU), Energianlegg (EA), and Lekeplass (o_LEK), outlining the intended use and regulations for each area.\n\nThe playground has been moved so that it does not affect the danger zone. Within green areas, only light interventions such as footpaths, benches, and signage are allowed, with measures in place for safety. Within zones for rockfall, avalanches, and high-voltage installations, only footpaths according to the outdoor plan and preliminary project are permitted. Quality requirements for playgrounds and outdoor recreation areas are specified in the city plan, with the playground located in a sunny area in the southeast.\n\nThe excerpt discusses the design and layout requirements for a playground area and a new building called Fjellstua. The playground area must be developed according to the outdoor plan, following universal design and technical regulations. The playground should be located away from pollutants, noise, traffic, and other health hazards. Winter use of the playground is linked to residential purposes. The new Fjellstua building should have a clear identity as an entrance to the mountain, with a functional roof design that also reflects a mountain landscape. The material used should blend with the natural surroundings, with raw and untreated surfaces to highlight the structural elements. The main structure is planned to be made of glued laminated timber.\n\nThe document is a plan description for the Fjellheisen Troms\u00f8 project by Hamran/Johansen Arkitekter AS. The plan includes a map of the area, the address, scale, area, and coordinates. The maximum height of the building is stated to be C+432M.\n\nByggets plassering og funksjon indikerer at det skal v\u00e6re synlig og ikke fors\u00f8kes skjult, med m\u00e5let om \u00e5 skape et signalbygg. Bygget skal harmonere godt med landskapet og vil se mer lavm\u00e6lt ut fra oversiden. Det planlagte nybygget vil ha en tillatt BRA p\u00e5 3000 m2, med to etasjer over terrengniv\u00e5 i bakkant. Det foreligger et samarbeidsprosjekt om utbedring av uteomr\u00e5dene p\u00e5 Fjellheisplat\u00e5et, som inkluderer bruk av stedlige masser til terrengbearbeiding. Byggingen av ny fjellstue vil medf\u00f8re uttak av ca. 800 m3 l\u00f8smasser, og det transportere disse massene ned fra fjellet er dyrt og lite b\u00e6rekraftig.\n\nDet blir foresl\u00e5tt \u00e5 omdisponere l\u00f8smassene fra et byggeprosjekt til opparbeidelsen av uteomr\u00e5dene p\u00e5 Fjellheisplat\u00e5et. Dette inkluderer \u00e5 fylle p\u00e5 l\u00f8smasser for etablering av en \u00absvevesti\u00bb til Storsteinen og ny lekeplass, samt \u00e5 fylle igjen og revegetere nedtr\u00e5kkede stier p\u00e5 plat\u00e5et. Omfordeling av l\u00f8smassene anses som god ressursbruk b\u00e5de i b\u00e6rekrafts- og samfunns\u00f8konomisk perspektiv. Parkering er ikke direkte knyttet til planen, men det p\u00e5pekes at en utvidelse og fornying av Fjellstua kan resultere i flere bes\u00f8kende som vil ha behov for parkering utenfor planomr\u00e5det.\n\nThe relationship between infrastructure and the proposed development at Fjellstua has been considered, including changes to access and parking, with a focus on ensuring smooth bus traffic flow without the need for reversing. Fjellheisen AS also plans to establish a shuttle bus to and from Troms\u00f8 city center to reduce traffic and parking needs. In terms of water and sewage infrastructure, calculations are based on a maximum daily consumption during Fjellstua's opening hours, with plans to utilize existing tanks for water storage and a recommended safety reserve in case of emergencies.\n\nBeskrivelsen av fjellheisen i Troms\u00f8 inkluderer vurderinger om \u00e5 dimensjonere buffertanken til \u00e5 ivareta brannvannskravet, samt avklaringer om slokkevannsbehov, spillvann og overvann. Det anbefales \u00e5 vurdere tiltak for \u00e5 \u00f8ke pumpekapasiteten for spillvann og planlegge for \u00f8kt takareal med utbyggingen av den nye Fjellstua. Brannstrategien b\u00f8r avklares med kommunen og brannvesenet f\u00f8r prosjekteringen.\n\nDet planlegges \u00e5 opparbeide eksisterende stier som grusstier/spaltede grusstier, samt en svevesti som skal g\u00e5 fra Fjellstua til utsiktspunktet ved Storsteinen. For svevestien er det planlagt \u00e5 benytte permeabelt dekke i form av gitterrister. Planomr\u00e5det er en del av to store nedb\u00f8rfelt, med avrenning mot Tromsdalen og Troms\u00f8ysundet. Tiltakene som er planlagt vil ikke p\u00e5virke eksisterende flomveier. Adkomsten til anlegget skjer via gondolbanen fra nedre stasjon, samt til fots fra Sherpatrappa.\n\nPlanen for utend\u00f8rsomr\u00e5det inkluderer opparbeidelse av eksisterende stier samt en svevesti fra Fjellstua til utsiktspunktet ved Storsteinen. Varelevering vil skje ved nedre stasjon med frakt til \u00f8vre stasjon via gondol. Tilgjengeligheten for g\u00e5ende og syklende vil bli ivaretatt ved hjelp av gondolbane, turstier, og rullestolheiser. Ingen nye offentlige anlegg planlegges, og milj\u00f8oppf\u00f8lgingsplan vil utarbeides for \u00e5 sikre milj\u00f8hensyn og oppn\u00e5 milj\u00f8m\u00e5lene i prosjektet.\n\nSpecial considerations that must be taken into account in the environmental monitoring plan include material selection, transportation/noise during construction, waste management, mass handling, and nature and biological diversity. The environmental monitoring plan should demonstrate how environmental considerations will be incorporated and followed during the design, contracting, and construction phases, in order to minimize the impact on the environment and those affected by the project. In addition to general societal interests, the environmental monitoring plan should also contribute to the well-being of those living in and using the areas around the Mountain Lift Plateau. Universal design and accessibility have been emphasized, with all public areas designed for universal access on one level, connected to the platform by an elevator. Robust materials will be used for physical adaptation to accommodate the large number of users and varied needs of user groups. Developed paths will effectively link existing elements such as the Sherpa stairs, Mountain Lodge, and Big Rock.\n\nUniversal accessibility between Fjellstua and Storsteinen is being developed, with surfaces suitable for wheelchair users and visually impaired individuals. The mountain lift is an important option for people who cannot access the mountains in other ways, so the area should be developed for maximum enjoyment by as many people as possible. Information points and seating areas will be established. The outdoor area covers approximately 80 daa from Fjellstua to Storsteinen, with a designated playground area southeast of Fjellstua. Lighting will be downward-facing and shielded to accommodate the visually impaired without creating light pollution, adhering to guidelines for the KULA landscape. Existing vegetation is of low quality and a robust pathway system will be created to minimize wear and tear and facilitate natural revegetation outside of the pathways.\n\nDet er viktig \u00e5 unng\u00e5 ferdsel utenfor tilrettelagte traseer og benytte det opparbeidede stinettet. Reguleringsomr\u00e5det best\u00e5r hovedsakelig av offentlige friomr\u00e5der, mens turveiene p\u00e5 fjellheisplat\u00e5et er knutepunkter for popul\u00e6re turstier. Adkomst til omr\u00e5det kan skje til fots eller via gondolbane. Det legges opp til \u00f8kt aktivitet b\u00e5de sommer og vinter, med aktiviteter som sykling, luftsport og skiturisme. Det m\u00e5 opprettes en utomhusplan og f\u00f8lges rekkef\u00f8lgebestemmelser f\u00f8r midlertidige tillatelser gis. Marksikring og tiltak rundt anleggsomr\u00e5det er n\u00f8ye planlagt for \u00e5 ivareta sikkerheten.\n\nEn merket sti for turister vil bli lagt utenfor byggegjerdet, og den vil knytte seg til en eksisterende tursti fra Sherpatrappa til Storsteinen. Innenfor anleggsomr\u00e5det er det avsatt tre lagringsomr\u00e5der og to sett med brakker. Det er ogs\u00e5 plass til to t\u00e5rnkraner, med fundament plassert ved fremtidig plassering av Fjellstua og \u00f8st for Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon. Helikopterlandingsplassen vil v\u00e6re plassert i ytterkant av omr\u00e5det.\n\nThe outdoor space plan for the trappa og Storsteine fjellheisen regulation minimizes impact on vegetation, with some areas being secured against landslides. Busslinje 26 provides public transport to the lower station of the Fjellheisen. Guidelines for managing cultural landscapes are in place to protect heritage sites in the area. The project does not directly affect known cultural monuments.\n\nA new station (Fjellstua) is being built along with a pedestrian bridge to Storsteinen and an open railing. Some paths in the area will be gravel or converted to crushed gravel paths. The direct impact of the project is considered small and not in conflict with guidelines for managing the KULA landscape. The project will have a positive effect on erosion and vegetation. The visual impact will be minimal on Sami cultural sites but more noticeable from the upper station of the mountain lift. Overall, the impact on cultural heritage viewpoints is slightly negative.\n\nThe document is a plan description for the Fjellheisen Troms\u00f8 project by Hamran/Johansen Arkitekter AS. It includes sections on social infrastructure, outdoor interests, water and sewage plans, and waste collection. The focus is on improving outdoor amenities while ensuring the project does not hinder public access and follows current waste management regulations.\n\nOppf\u00f8lging og l\u00f8sninger for u\u00f8nskede hendelser i forbindelse med planforslaget inkluderer revisjon eller utarbeidelse av beredskapsplaner, vurderinger av omr\u00e5destabilitet, etablering av beredskapsvei til planomr\u00e5det, inngjerding som hindrer klatring, og etablering av et beredskapslager med vanndunker. Rekkef\u00f8lgebestemmelser inneb\u00e6rer at midlertidig brukstillatelse eller ferdigattest ikke kan gis f\u00f8r visse krav, som godkjenning av lekeplasser, er oppfylt. Se vedlegg 04 for fullstendig risiko- og s\u00e5rbarhetsanalyse.\n\nF\u00f8r det kan gis midlertidig brukstillatelse eller ferdigattest, m\u00e5 det foreligge en godkjent VA-ferdigmelding for privat VAO-infrastruktur og tilkoblinger til offentlig nett. Konsekvensutredning er ikke relevant if\u00f8lge kapittel 2.4, og planforslaget vil endre arealform\u00e5let til Bebyggelse og anlegg, gr\u00f8nnstruktur, landbruks-, tur- og friluftsform\u00e5l samt reindrift. Oppgraderingen av fjellheisens \u00f8vre stasjon vil ha en negativ lokal p\u00e5virkning p\u00e5 landskapsbildet, men liten eller ingen konsekvens samlet sett. Utbyggingen vil p\u00e5virke registrerte naturtyper og arter, spesielt naturtypelokaliteten Storsteinen 2.\n\n\u00c5 tilrettelegge og kanalisere ferdsel mellom Fjellstua og Storsteinen vil redusere direkte slitasje og bidra til naturlig revegetering. \u00d8kt ferdsel innover Fl\u00f8ya kan p\u00e5virke naturtypelokaliteten negativt, da den har h\u00f8y kvalitet og er r\u00f8dlistet. Tiltak som kan samle ferdsel vil v\u00e6re viktig. Planlagte utomhusomr\u00e5der har som m\u00e5l \u00e5 beskytte bunnvegetasjon og styre trafikken mot gangbaner for \u00e5 begrense skade p\u00e5 marka. Solforholdene for omr\u00e5det vil ha minimale endringer med den nye Fjellstua.\n\nSummary: The document discusses a new mountain lift in Troms\u00f8, Norway. The area will still be perceived as an outdoor area, with a more defined trail network resulting in more vegetation. The upper station of the lift will be visible from certain viewpoints but will have minimal impact on the cultural environment. The project does not directly affect known cultural sites and includes a new station and walkway.\n\nDet vurderes at tiltaket har en liten direkte p\u00e5virkning p\u00e5 kulturmilj\u00f8et og er i samsvar med retningslinjene for forvaltningen av KULA-landskapet. Tiltaket vil ber\u00f8re en mindre viktig del av kulturmilj\u00f8et med lite arealbeslag, noe som kan f\u00f8re til noe forringelse. N\u00e6rvirkningene av tiltaket anses som positive da det kan redusere erosjon og bidra til reetablering av naturlig vegetasjon. Samarbeidet med Troms\u00f8 kommune har resultert i en god s\u00e5rbarhetsvurdering og kunnskapsgrunnlaget anses som tilstrekkelig. F\u00f8re-var-prinsippet fokuserer p\u00e5 de p\u00e5virkede naturtypelokalitetene, hvor s\u00e6rlig \"Storsteinen 2\" har sv\u00e6rt lav kvalitet og redusert tilstand i dag.\n\nEn tilrettelegging for ferdsel mellom Fjellstua og Storsteinen vil v\u00e6re positivt ved \u00e5 redusere slitasje og legge til rette for revegetering. Planlagte tiltak vurderes \u00e5 ha sm\u00e5 konsekvenser, og et samlet kostnadssynspunkt tas hensyn til. Tiltakshaveren skal dekke kostnadene ved eventuell skade p\u00e5 naturmangfoldet, og milj\u00f8forsvarlige teknikker og driftsmetoder skal benyttes for \u00e5 begrense skader p\u00e5 naturen.\n\nThe project aims to improve recreational activities by creating new hiking trails, a warm room, and a caf\u00e9 at Fjellheisplat\u00e5et. The area serves as a hub for popular hiking trails and efforts will be made to reduce damage to vegetation and trails. Access to the area is primarily through a gondola or hiking trails. The project also aligns with guidelines to enhance children's interests in planning and provides safe areas for them to play and explore. There are no significant risks associated with pollution, noise, or traffic hazards in the area.\n\nOppholdsarealene mellom Fjellstua og Storsteinen blir forbedret med bedre stinettverk og lekeplass. Omr\u00e5det vil tilrettelegge for ulike typer lek p\u00e5 ulike \u00e5rstider, med turstier om sommeren og skif\u00f8re om vinteren. Det vil ogs\u00e5 v\u00e6re en varmestue p\u00e5 Fjellstua egnet for vinterbruk. Utsiktspunkter og uteoppholdsarealer vil v\u00e6re tilgjengelige for ulike aldersgrupper og fremme sosialt samspill. Videref\u00f8ring og utvidelse av turstier vil forbedre den sosiale infrastrukturen, og tiltakene vil legge til rette for universell tilgjengelighet slik at alle kan nyte friluftslivet i omr\u00e5det. Energibruk og klimagassutslipp vil bli vurdert i henhold til TEK17 under byggesaken.\n\nOppvarmingssystemet for et bygg med over 1000m2 skal dekke minimum 60% av varmebehovet med energifleksible varmesystemer som tillater bruk av ulike varmekilder som vann og luft. Lavtemperatur varmel\u00f8sninger skal ogs\u00e5 tilrettelegges for effektiv bruk av spillvarme, solvarme og omgivelsesvarme. Det er ikke tillatt \u00e5 bruke fossilt brensel til oppvarming eller varmtvann. Et klimagassregnskap basert p\u00e5 norsk standard m\u00e5 utarbeides, og klimagassbudsjettet skal brukes aktivt for \u00e5 redusere utslipp under prosjektering og utf\u00f8relse.\n\nThe requirement for a greenhouse gas calculation is based on parts of the Norwegian Standard NS 3720:2018 Method for greenhouse gas calculations for buildings. The requirement does not cover all building elements and life cycle modules listed in the standard. Building elements should generally be included in the accounts at a two-digit level. For building element 21, only pile foundations and direct foundations must be included. Biogenic carbon (from, for example, wood-based products) is not included in the account. Waste from the construction site should also be included in the accounts. There should be a 50-year calculation period (lifespan). Third-party approved, standardized, and life-cycle-based documentation for greenhouse gas emissions should be used as documentation for the greenhouse gas account, such as an Environmental Product Declaration (EPD). If specific documentation for the product group is not available, generic (average) greenhouse gas values from national databases can be used, with a 25 percent markup if not already included. A specific guidance document has been developed to meet the documentation requirements for greenhouse gas accounts: \"Guide for the preparation of greenhouse gas accounts\".\n\nMulticonsult's ROS analysis concludes that the avalanche event is in the yellow danger zone, while the wind is in the red danger zone. The cable car and water and sewage systems are in the green danger zone. The cable car and water and sewage systems are considered to have low uncertainty, while the avalanche and wind events have medium uncertainty. Proposed measures for the area include revising/developing a contingency plan, establishing an emergency route to the area, and setting up emergency water storage at the upper and lower stations. This section does not address soil resources/agriculture. The technical infrastructure section includes a plan for water and sewage infrastructure and the use of an existing energy facility on the site. The economic consequences for the municipality are discussed in terms of the financial sustainability of the cable car, which has been important to Troms\u00f8 and the surrounding region since its opening in 1961.\n\nI 2019 hadde fjellheisen i Troms\u00f8 250.000 gjester fra hele verden, i tillegg til 100.000 som bes\u00f8kte Fjellstua via Sherpatrappa eller andre stier. Bygningene p\u00e5 toppen av fjellet er gamle og slitt, og ikke egnet for s\u00e5 mange bes\u00f8kende. Det er behov for oppgraderinger for \u00e5 forbedre sanit\u00e6re forhold, servering og sikkerhet. En plan for en ny Fjellstua inkluderer en kafe, restaurant, bar og suvenirbutikk. Tiltakene vil ogs\u00e5 forbedre sikkerheten og kanalisere trafikken for \u00e5 redusere slitasje p\u00e5 naturen. Det er viktig \u00e5 ivareta milj\u00f8- og landskapsverdiene i omr\u00e5det med tanke p\u00e5 b\u00e5de innbyggere og turister.\n\nProsjektet for opparbeidelse av uteomr\u00e5dene skal forhindre forringelse av naturen og gj\u00f8re omr\u00e5det mer tilgjengelig for bevegelseshemmede. Innspill fra Avinor og NVE om belysning og forebyggende tiltak mot fugler blir delvis tatt til f\u00f8lge i planleggingsprosessen.\n\nDen generelle veilederen for planarbeidet inneholder innspill om universell tilgjengelighet mellom Fjellstua og Storsteinen, samt infopunkter og sitteplasser. Det anbefales \u00e5 bruke Vegvesenets h\u00e5ndbok V129 Universell utforming av veger og gater i planleggingen, men det antas at det ikke er n\u00f8dvendig \u00e5 gj\u00f8re den juridisk bindende. Sitteplasser i tilknytning til universelt utformet gangvei er allerede inkludert i planene.\n\nGangbaner som er brattere enn tillatt i TEK17 p\u00e5 kort distanse vil bli vanskelig \u00e5 opprettholde p\u00e5 mykt opparbeidede gangveger. Det anbefales \u00e5 beskrive klimautslipp, transport av materialer og ta hensyn til kulturminnevern under planlegging av prosjektet. Ambisjonen er \u00e5 ha lavt klimagassutslipp og n\u00f8ye transportplanlegging. Hensynssone for kulturminnevern b\u00f8r ikke dekke hele planomr\u00e5det.\n\nDet m\u00e5 utarbeides bestemmelser om at bygging ikke kan skje utover tillatelsen som er gitt. Deler av omr\u00e5det m\u00e5 avsettes som gr\u00f8ntomr\u00e5der. Omr\u00e5der som ikke skal bebygges b\u00f8r avsettes som LNFR-form\u00e5l. Det b\u00f8r legges opp til hel\u00e5rig, d\u00f8gn\u00e5pne toalettl\u00f8sninger for allmennheten. Det er behov for en helhetlig strategisk tiln\u00e6rming til Fjellheisplat\u00e5et.\n\nVi ber om \u00e5 se p\u00e5 ulike virkemidler som kan sikre at tiltakshaver oppfyller sine forpliktelser overfor omr\u00e5dene rundt. Dette gj\u00f8res som en del av prosjekteringen av utomhusarealene i samarbeid mellom Troms\u00f8 kommune og Fjellheisen AS. Fylkeskommunen er uenige i at sentrale problemstillinger som infrastruktur og parkering ikke blir ivaretatt i detaljreguleringen av konkrete tiltak. Planavgrensningen og influensomr\u00e5det er gjort i samarbeid med planmyndighetene. St\u00f8yproblemer under anleggsfasen, spesielt fra frakt av materialer med helikopter, vil bli adressert i planbeskrivelsen. SOSI-fil og PDF av plankartet er sendt til Kartverket p\u00e5 e-post.\n\nDe gjeldende retningslinjene for st\u00f8y m\u00e5 f\u00f8lges, men det kan s\u00f8kes om dispensasjon fra st\u00f8yregelverket for deler av arbeidene. Effektene p\u00e5 naturmangfoldet og landskapet m\u00e5 unders\u00f8kes av en utreder med kompetanse p\u00e5 naturforvaltning og landskapsverdier. Sveveveier og rigg- og anleggsomr\u00e5der m\u00e5 ogs\u00e5 vurderes n\u00f8ye og ulike alternativer m\u00e5 utredes. Gangbanene planlegges for minst mulig inngrep i naturen og best mulig fremkommelighet. En rigg- og marksikringsplan m\u00e5 ogs\u00e5 utarbeides og sendes p\u00e5 h\u00f8ring.\n\nStatsforvalteren mener det er n\u00f8dvendig med medvirkning og faglige innspill fra sektormyndigheter. Rigging- og marksikringplanen skal legges ved planforslaget p\u00e5 h\u00f8ring. Det blir ogs\u00e5 vist til prinsippene i naturmangfoldloven og at bygg i planomr\u00e5det b\u00f8r oppf\u00f8res med passiv- eller plusshusstandard. Utbygger anbefales \u00e5 bruke lokale energil\u00f8sninger og materialer i byggefasen.\n\nStatsforvalteren anbefaler at det utarbeides et klimagassregnskap i planprosessen, med fokus p\u00e5 tiltak for \u00e5 redusere energiforbruk, klimagassutslipp, og valg av energil\u00f8sninger og byggematerialer. De ber ogs\u00e5 at planbeskrivelsen dr\u00f8fter hvordan utbyggingen vil bidra til \u00e5 n\u00e5 b\u00e6rekraftsm\u00e5lene. Videre mener de at det b\u00f8r legges vekt p\u00e5 \u00e5 informere allmennheten om planprosessen og \u00f8nske innspill, samt at planen b\u00f8r legges fram i Planforum f\u00f8r offentlig ettersyn. Til slutt, de ber kommunen om \u00e5 sende planavgrensningen som SOSI-fil og PDF-utskrift til Kartverket. Disse anbefalingene ble ikke fulgt, da nybygg allerede f\u00f8lger strenge energikrav, medvirkning i plansaker f\u00f8lger loven, og planforum vurderes ikke som hensiktsmessig i denne saken.\n\nKartverket \u00f8nsker at forslag til plankart sendes som SOSI-fil og PDF-utskrift p\u00e5 e-post f\u00f8r h\u00f8ring. En planbeskrivelse for Fjellheisen i Troms\u00f8 inneholder merknader fra Statens vegvesen og S\u00e1mediggi/Sametinget, blant annet om parkering og reindrift. Statens vegvesen mener parkeringsl\u00f8sninger b\u00f8r omtales i planen, mens Sametinget \u00f8nsker mer informasjon om hvordan planen vil p\u00e5virke reindriftsomr\u00e5der. Kanalisering og styring av ferdselen i omr\u00e5det er positivt for reindriften if\u00f8lge Sametinget.\n\nSametinget \u00f8nsker at reinbeitedistriktet skal v\u00e6re involvert i planleggingen av Fjellheisen i Troms\u00f8, selv om planomr\u00e5det har blitt innskrenket og virkningen av tiltaket er redusert. De \u00f8nsker at bebyggelsen harmoniseres med fjellet og landskapet, og at informasjonstiltak om reindrift samordnes med turistinformasjon. Det er planlagt \u00e5 bygge ut omr\u00e5det i ett trinn, med minimal masseuttak og transport av anleggsmaskiner med helikopter. Forebyggende tiltak vil bli gjort for \u00e5 minimere skader p\u00e5 terrenget og vegetasjonen under utbyggingen. Bygget skal v\u00e6re tilpasset moderne behov, med fokus p\u00e5 milj\u00f8, b\u00e6rekraft og tilgjengelighet for alle.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an urban planner at Troms\u00f8 municipality, informs the recipient that the proposal for plan 1956 regarding the upper station of Fjellheisen has been made available for public scrutiny. She provides links to the documents and states that the deadline for feedback is January 11, 2024. The email includes attachments of the notification letter and list. Sundf\u00f8r's contact information is also provided for any questions or concerns.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r provided feedback to Lars Hamran regarding a draft plan for the Fjellheisen upper station before their meeting on March 28, 2023. She mentioned that some agreed-upon details were missing from the plan, such as the rigging and construction area, and requested further clarification during the meeting. She also inquired about the possibility of coordinating the plan proposal with the building permit application. Additionally, she suggested contacting a specific individual for assistance with the drawing of the plan. Lars had previously sent the draft plan in PDF format as requested.This document is a notification of a public hearing and consultation for the detailed planning of the upper station of the Fjellheisen cable car in Troms\u00f8. Stakeholders are invited to submit comments or objections by January 11, 2024. The document provides information on where to view the proposed plan and how to obtain copies of related documents. The communication includes a list of recipients, including government agencies, businesses, organizations, and individuals.The document is a letter from S\u00e5mediggi/Sametinget regarding the proposed development of the Fjellheisen upper station in Troms\u00f8. They state that they have no cultural heritage objections to the plan and believe it is well-designed to protect the National Cultural Landscape area. They emphasize the importance of consulting with the reindeer herding authority and relevant reindeer grazing districts. The letter is signed by Bj\u00f8rn Berg and Jon Gunnar Blom.There have been discussions about noise forecasts for the transportation of materials for Plan 1956 Fjellheisen. Suggestions have been made regarding specifying time intervals for activities and the number of those affected. The communication also includes details about proposed changes to noise documentation requirements in the building phase. The architects have been consulting with a noise expert and have considered the impact of helicopter and daily flight noise on the overall assessment. They plan to provide more detailed information in the building permit application once more project details are known.Lars Hamran is contacting Margareth Sundf\u00f8r about a preliminary assessment from Multiconsult regarding helicopter noise during the construction phase. They suggest addressing this issue as part of the building permit process and ask if it is possible to include a provision for such an assessment.Lars Hamran is inquiring about the possibility of creating an outdoor space plan in 1:1000 scale instead of the required 1:500 scale due to concerns about the size of the format. Margareth Sundf\u00f8r responds that she is working on a meeting summary and will send it after Easter.Lars Hamran inquires about the need for further evaluation under the KU regulation due to the deposition of excess masses. Margareth Sundf\u00f8r responds, stating that while the deposition itself does not require evaluation, it should have been considered in the initial assessment. She emphasizes the importance of thorough evaluations related to environmental and community impacts, as suggested by Statsforvalteren. She advises Hamran to ensure that the deposition of excess masses is addressed in the plan proposal.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r from Troms\u00f8 Kommune inquired about the availability of a shuttle bus from the city center to Fjellheisen. Ulf Johansen confirmed that the shuttle bus service was discontinued from June to October due to poor economic viability. Sundf\u00f8r asked if the shuttle service could be reinstated for the upcoming summer season, as it was mentioned in the plan description. Roger Fagerheim also followed up regarding the delayed deadline for feedback on plan 1956 Fjellheisen upper station.The email exchange is regarding the submission of a comprehensive risk and vulnerability assessment report (ROS) for a specific project. There were some issues with updating information in the report, and efforts are being made to clarify the situation with the municipal department. A geologist has provided input on landslide assessments for the project, which will be included as an attachment to the ROS report. There is also mention of a revised report regarding the validity and quality of another geological report related to the project. Additional updates to the ROS analysis may be made based on this new information.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an area planner at the Troms\u00f8 municipality, has received feedback on the plan for the Fjellheisen upper station. She has forwarded the comments from the Statsforvalteren to stakeholders and plans to review them in the coming week. The Statsforvalteren and Troms fylkeskommune requested an extension for their statements, which was granted. Stakeholders are eager to receive and discuss the feedback.Lars sent Margareth the requested documents, but she found that the checklist, cover letter, and plan description were missing. She asked Lars to send these documents and mentioned the importance of filling out the checklist with the delivery dates of each document.Lars is confirming the deadline for their plan proposal and asking if they can deliver it by the end of the day on Friday to be included in a meeting on October 2nd.In this email correspondence, Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an urban planner at Troms\u00f8 municipality, discusses the potential objections raised by Avinor regarding bird strike prevention measures in various development plans. She explains that Avinor has not raised objections to the Fjellheisen project, despite initial concerns, and provides details of the municipality's meetings and communications with Avinor on the matter. Journalist Ingvill Hafver from Byggeindustrien/ bygg.no asks for information about Avinor's objections to other development projects in Troms\u00f8.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an urban planner at Troms\u00f8 kommune, thanks the recipients for their feedback on a report from Skred AS. She highlights a critical area near Fjellheisen where the removal of trees could pose a risk to existing buildings. She suggests a team meeting to discuss potential actions, particularly in areas designated for a new mountain lodge. She attaches alternative zoning maps for review and invites relevant parties from Skred AS to the meeting. Margareth emphasizes that all email communications are subject to public disclosure.Lars Hamran, an architect from Hamran/Johansen Arkitekter AS in Norway, sent a revised plan initiative for the Fjellheisen project to the Postmottak Troms\u00f8 kommune and Margareth Sundf\u00f8r. The email included an attachment of the revised plan and contact information for Lars Hamran.Andre Johansen from Hamran/Johansen Arkitekter AS is providing Margareth Sundf\u00f8r with information on the area layout of a building. The existing mountain lodge is approximately 720m2 with a terrace of around 400m2. They are planning to enclose much of the current terrace, increasing the Gross Floor Area (BRA), as well as adding a new floor in parts of the building. Johansen hopes this clarifies the situation.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r is requesting missing documents for plan proposal 1956 Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon from Lars Hamran. She has downloaded the documents sent via WeTransfer but found that the checklist, cover letter, and plan description are missing. She asks Lars to send these documents and mentions the importance of providing a completed checklist with delivery dates. Sundf\u00f8r also inquires about the status of the acceptance letter from VA on the VAO frame plan.The municipality of Troms\u00f8 has received input from architect Amundsen AS regarding the design of the upper station of the mountain elevator project. They are suggesting minor changes to the regulation plan 1956 'Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon'. The plan includes regulated building boundaries, planned structures, and regulated height curves to guide development. They question the necessity of regulating planned structures when there is already a building boundary in place.\n\nBy regulating planned construction with an outline, changes to the project outside the specified line are not possible without a dispensation. Planned construction thus serves the same practical function as the building boundary. An illustration project attached to the zoning plan documents serves as a basis for further work and realization of the new upper station.\n\nByggherren \u00f8nsker \u00e5 fortsette med realiseringen av illustrasjonsprosjektet, men det krever dispensasjoner fra plankartet som har v\u00e6rt p\u00e5 h\u00f8ring. Dette inkluderer at perrongetasjen og gangvegen fra perrongetasjen opp til fjellstua er mer enn 2 meter utenfor planlagt bebyggelse, samt behovet for mer areal ved inngangspartiet og amfiet p\u00e5 grunn av plassering av planlagt bygg inntil byggegrensen mot s\u00f8r\u00f8st. Flytting av byggegrensen 3 meter mot s\u00f8r er \u00f8nskelig for \u00e5 kunne l\u00f8se disse utfordringene.\n\nThe document outlines proposed changes to a building plan for the upper station of a mountain elevator. The changes aim to avoid the need for multiple waivers, improve safety, and optimize the building design. Key changes include removing planned building lines to allow more flexibility in construction, adjusting building boundaries to accommodate terrain features, and adding provisions for emergency exits and water tanks. The proposed changes are intended to streamline the construction process and enhance the overall project design.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an urban planner at Troms\u00f8 Municipality, discusses the importance of including a provision for downward lighting in the detailed regulations for the Fjellheisen project. She highlights the benefits of such a provision, including improving air safety, reducing light pollution, and promoting public health. She also suggests looking at a legal thesis on light pollution for further information. Sundf\u00f8r emphasizes the need for compliance with planning regulations and the potential need for dispensation if the lighting requirements are not met.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an area planner from the City Planning Department in Troms\u00f8, is organizing a neighborhood meeting to discuss the detailed planning of the upper station of Fjellheisen. She is suggesting to hold the meeting on Teams but is open to a physical meeting if preferred. Sundf\u00f8r provides potential dates for the meeting in October and asks for availability. She also inquires about the municipality's contact person for the project and whether to communicate with both Roger Fagerheim and Lars Hamran.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r has sent an email to Lars Hamran, forwarding a map package prepared by Geodata for plan 1956 Fjellheisen upper station. She is an urban planner at the City Planning Section of Troms\u00f8 municipality. The email also includes her contact information and a reminder that all emails to Troms\u00f8 municipality are subject to the Public Records Act.A complaint has been lodged against the decision on detailed regulation for the upper station of Fjellheisen in Troms\u00f8. The complainant believes they have the right to appeal due to the potential impact on them and other residents in the area, given the expected increase in visitors to Fjellheisen. They argue that the plan did not adequately address the consequences of increased traffic and the effects on the local community.\n\nVi mener at planen ikke oppfyller kravene til planinitiativ i henhold til forskriften om behandling av private forslag til detaljregulering. Vi som beboere i influensomr\u00e5det knyttet til trafikkp\u00e5virkning burde v\u00e6rt hensyntatt i planleggingsprosessen, som beskrevet i veilederen for saksbehandling av Plan- og bygningsloven. Manglende varsling av direkte ber\u00f8rte parter anses som en saksbehandlingsfeil.\n\nBeboere i omr\u00e5det f\u00f8ler seg oversett i planleggingen av en ny plan og mener at de ikke har f\u00e5tt mulighet til \u00e5 delta aktivt i prosessen. De p\u00e5peker at planleggingen ikke har v\u00e6rt i samsvar med kravene i plan- og bygningsloven n\u00e5r det gjelder \u00e5penhet, forutsigbarhet og medvirkning. Beboerne \u00f8nsker ikke \u00e5 stoppe utbyggingen, men h\u00e5per at deres klage kan f\u00f8re til at trafikksituasjonen i omr\u00e5det tas p\u00e5 alvor f\u00f8r ytterligere aktivitet settes i gang. De \u00f8nsker at vedtaket om planen oppheves og at saken sendes tilbake til kommunens administrasjon for \u00e5 utrede trafikksituasjonen grundigere.\n\nBefore the plan can be finalized, an assessment of the traffic situation in the area needs to be done, considering how it will be affected by the development and how the municipality and developers can contribute to ensuring a safe traffic situation and a good residential environment for those living in the area. Concerns have been raised about the lack of traffic-related measures in the plan, with calls for specific actions such as moving the bus stop and establishing a sidewalk to ensure safety for pedestrians, especially school children. Concerns have also been expressed about the expected increase in visitors to the area due to the development. Various stakeholders have highlighted the potential impact on traffic and the need to address it in the detailed regulation plan. Despite feedback from public authorities and residents, the plan has not taken into account the traffic situation in the area, leading to a sense of being disregarded by those affected. Residents describe the current traffic situation as unsafe, particularly for pedestrians and school children, with narrow roads and overcrowded bus stops causing difficulties for local residents.Hanne Lunde Sveen-Vangen from Troms\u00f8 and Finnmark county council hopes to be kept informed about the progress of the process regarding the regulation of the mountain elevator. They are open to dialogue with the municipality regarding the traffic challenges and do not have any specific demands on the developer at this stage. Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an urban planner from Troms\u00f8 municipality, does not have any additional information beyond what was discussed at the initial meeting regarding the traffic situation. They mention that the details will be handled in other processes at a later stage.Frabene AS has concerns about the uncertainty surrounding the regulation process for the Fjellheisen project. They request clarification from the city's urban development department on whether the summary accurately reflects the municipality's position. Frabene AS highlights their preference to avoid detailed regulation and challenges the extensive input from the meeting, which they believe would effectively reset the entire project. They seek a prompt resolution, potentially through a clarification meeting.Roger Fagerheim sent an email to Margareth Sundf\u00f8r providing feedback on the meeting minutes regarding the collaboration with PIF and the boundary of the planning area. He suggested more specific descriptions and additions to the minutes. Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, in her email, thanked everyone for the meeting and shared the proposed minutes for feedback. She requested input on the accuracy of names and affiliations in the minutes and mentioned the deadline for feedback.The document is a letter regarding the initiation of a detailed regulation plan for the upper station of Fjellheisen. The fee for this plan is determined by Troms\u00f8 municipality's fee schedule for urban development and is set at kr. 109,400. The fee will be invoiced during the announcement of the plan's commencement. If the case is withdrawn before the announcement, fees will be charged based on elapsed time. The letter includes detailed information on the fee breakdown based on different parameters.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r confirms that the detailed regulation for the Fjellheisen project must be approved by KOBY before being presented to the municipal council for final approval. The administration is planning for the matter to be considered at the KOBY meeting on March 7th. The decision on whether to proceed with political handling in March or later will be made after approval from the management. Roger Fagerheim from Frabene AS expresses the company's desire to start construction on the Fjellstua project in May and seeks clarification on the timeline for approval at KOBY and the municipal council. He emphasizes the importance of a quick approval process for obtaining the necessary building permits.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r provides feedback on the draft advertisement for the start notice, suggesting changes to detail regulations in order to comply with the law. She requests an updated advertisement be sent to her for review before it is posted on the municipality's website. Lars Hamran, the architect, acknowledges the feedback and asks if there is anything else that should be included in the advertisement.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r from the Section for Urban Development at the Municipality of Troms\u00f8, received an updated note from Skred AS regarding the safety zone for the forest area. She found that it addressed the issue of danger to the buildings below the planned area in a clear manner. They will incorporate parts of the text into the project description and attach the note as Appendix 19. Andre Johansen from Hamran/Johansen Architects provided the updated note arguing that NGls map polygon should be restricted and not affect the planned area.The upper station of Fjellheisen plan 1956 has had its deadline for feedback extended at the request of the County Governor and the County Municipality. The County Governor has been granted an extended deadline until January 18th, and the County Municipality until January 15th.Lars Hamran confirms receipt of the meeting minutes and clarifies the correct email address for his company, Hamran/Johansen Arkitekter AS. Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an urban planner from Troms\u00f8 kommune, sends the meeting minutes and presentation, requesting feedback by a specific date. She also asks for confirmation of the correct email address for Lars Hamran and accurate representation of names in the minutes.Lars Hamran sent an email to Margareth Sundf\u00f8r and Rune Hjallar regarding feedback on a draft advertisement for the start of detailed planning for the upper station of Fjellheisen and notification of parallel processing of the building case. Lars mentioned that including parallel processing in the notification is to keep options open and a decision will be made later. He has already sent the ad for publication in Nordlys and Troms\u00f8. Margareth suggested specifying in the title that the ad is about the upper station of Fjellheisen. The municipality is okay with notifying parallel processing of the detailed planning and building case.\n\nDet er diskutert muligheten for \u00e5 legge til rette for parallell behandling av detaljregulering og byggesak i forbindelse med prosjektet Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon. Kommunen er \u00e5pen for dette, men p\u00e5peker at de ikke har bestemmelser for effektiv parallell saksbehandling i delegasjonsreglementet. Det er usikkert hvor mye tid som vil spares, men kommunen vil v\u00e6re behjelpelig med koordinering. Utbygger m\u00e5 v\u00e6re klar over risikoen knyttet til parallell behandling og at kommunen ikke vil gi dispensasjon for igangsetting av deler av tiltaket underveis i prosessen.\u00f8ylen inntas,tv'en settes p\u00e5 konkurransevinn,popkornene sprettes og sofaen blir okkupert.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r requests a meeting regarding Plan 1956 Fjellheisen, but asks for the progress plan and more information before confirming. She also asks for all feedback received and their assessment, as well as a proposal for the progress plan discussed at a previous meeting. Lars Hamran had previously mentioned a progress plan and requested a meeting to discuss the process further.Avinor has provided a response to the public consultation on the detailed zoning plan for the upper station of Fjellheisen. They acknowledge that there is no provision for preventive measures against birdstrike near Troms\u00f8 Airport in the plan, but since the area is on the outskirts and has limited access to food for birds, they accept this omission. Avinor has no further comments on the plan.Statsforvalteren i Troms og Finnmark har mottatt en h\u00f8ringsuttalelse ang\u00e5ende reguleringsplanen for Fjellstua i Troms\u00f8 kommune. Planen inkluderer bygging av ny fjellstue og kanalisering av ferdsel for \u00e5 minimere skade p\u00e5 vegetasjon og s\u00f8rge for sikkerhet. Statsforvalteren mener planen mangler konkrete tiltak for \u00e5 h\u00e5ndtere masseturisme og kanalisere ferdselen effektivt. De oppfordrer kommunen til \u00e5 inkludere flere avb\u00f8tende tiltak i planen og understreker betydningen av \u00e5 ta hensyn til reindriften og naturmangfoldet.ycopi sendes til SAMEDIGGI / SAMETINGET og Troms fylkeskommune.Lars Hamran sent an email to Margareth Sundf\u00f8r and Erik Eidesen regarding a plan for the transportation of machines for construction purposes. He attached a document outlining the plan and requested that necessary clarifications be made with the relevant departments in the municipality.Hamran/Johansen Arkitekter AS sends a detailed regulatory plan for the Fjellheisen upper station to Troms\u00f8 municipality. The plan has been developed in collaboration with stakeholders and takes into account feedback from public consultations. The proposed development has a long history and is part of a larger project. The architect highlights the thorough work done on the project and the positive response from the municipality.Marijne Janssens from Arkitektkontoret Amundsen AS is discussing the need for a provision allowing for terrain adjustments for the emergency exit at the Fjellheisen upper station. Margareth Sundf\u00f8r from Troms\u00f8 Kommune is seeking clarification on the dimensions of the proposed adjustments. This is part of their ongoing discussions regarding the development of the Fjellheisen upper station and its regulatory plan.Lars Hamran emailed Margareth Sundf\u00f8r inquiring about a new date for a neighborhood meeting at Fjellheisen upper station, which had been postponed. Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an urban planner, responded that the meeting had been delayed and a new date would be proposed soon.This is a response to a received complaint regarding a planning decision for the Fjellheisen upper station. The complaint has been acknowledged and will be processed within 3 months. If the complaint is not upheld, it will be transferred to the State Governor of Troms and Finnmark for a final decision. The response is signed by Rigmor Tonstad, Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, and others from the City Planning Department.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r forwarded an email regarding feedback on a ROS analysis for the Fjellheisen upper station plan. Lars Hamran was unable to be reached, so Andre Johansen was copied. Sundf\u00f8r expressed concerns about the lack of follow-up on their feedback in the plan proposal, and stated that the plan could not be considered complete until an updated ROS analysis was provided. Lars Hamran forwarded the latest ROS analysis with relevant changes, and Pia Nordb\u00f8 from Multiconsult clarified details about safety barriers in the analysis.This email is a response to a complaint regarding the approved regulation plan for the Fjellheisen project. The sender argues that the issues raised by the complainants regarding traffic and the impact on residents have been considered in the planning process and appropriate measures have been taken. They highlight excerpts from the plan description and the municipal council's decision to support their argument. The sender also mentions that they have agreed to move a bus stop to improve traffic conditions and will provide shuttle bus services. They believe that accommodating the complaints would not change the outcome of the process and may lead to unnecessary delays in the project. They support the council's decision to address traffic issues in a larger context through separate regulations.Lone Alien H\u00f8gda sent a response acknowledging receipt of the meeting minutes from the Birdstrike meeting and stating that they will be included in the final report. Erik Eidesen from Troms\u00f8 Municipality replied, mentioning that the municipality expects Avinor to respond to a letter regarding birdstrike-related issues to clarify the legal and professional basis for objections to detailed zoning plans.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r is requesting an updated Risk and Vulnerability analysis for a proposed plan for the upper station of Fjellheisen. The analysis provided was dated April 28, 2023, which seems to be the same report previously submitted to the municipality on May 3 of the same year. The plan will not be considered complete until an updated analysis is provided.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an area planner in the City Planning section of Troms\u00f8 Municipality, sent an email requesting the Politisk sekretariat to forward the information regarding the public consultation and hearing on Plan 1956 for the upper station of Fjellheisen to the Municipal Council for People with Disabilities and the Elderly Council. The deadline for feedback is January 11, 2024, and the documents can be found in the meeting calendar or on the municipality's website. Sundf\u00f8r provided her contact information for any queries.Mattilsynet has reviewed the plan for the development of the Fjellheisen upper station and Fjellstua in Troms\u00f8. They have evaluated the water supply, specifically the availability of safe drinking water and firewater for the area. They emphasize the importance of protecting drinking water sources and preventing contamination. Mattilsynet has no further comments on the matter.Statens Vegvesen varsler om oppstart av detaljregulering for Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon og omr\u00e5det rundt Fjellstua i Troms\u00f8 kommune. Planen inneb\u00e6rer regulering av etablert arealbruk og legge til rette for nybygg, inkludert opparbeiding av utend\u00f8rsarealer mot Storsteinen. Statens vegvesen uttaler seg om adkomst og parkering, og mener disse m\u00e5 tas hensyn til i planarbeidet. Planen vil ikke ha vesentlige virkninger for milj\u00f8 og samfunn sammenlignet med dagens situasjon.Lars Hamran sent a draft of an advertisement for the Fjellheisen project to Margareth Sundf\u00f8r for review. Sundf\u00f8r suggested some changes, including replacing \"reguleringsplan\" with \"detaljregulering\" for clarity. She also requested an updated version of the advertisement for communication purposes. Hamran responded, incorporating her feedback and asking if the changes were acceptable.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r is responding to an email concerning a contract with Troms\u00f8 municipality regarding Plan 1956 Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon. She confirms that the matter is being followed up by the section leader in urban development. She explains that meeting minutes may end up on the public mailing list due to transparency laws. She emphasizes that all emails to Troms\u00f8 municipality are handled according to the law and may be made public.\n\nRoger Fagerheim followed up on the agreement with PIF regarding the mountain plateau, and mentioned the challenge of keeping meeting minutes private due to the policy of transparency. Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an urban planner, explained that all documents are archived according to public disclosure laws to ensure transparency in public decision-making.\n\nRoger Fagerheim from Frabene AS is inquiring about the progress on a certain agreement with PIF regarding the Fjellheisplat\u00e5et. He also expresses concerns about a recent news article in Nordlys that may have inaccurately portrayed the company's plans for an access road in Tromsdalen. Erik Eidesen from Troms\u00f8 kommune is copied on the email.\n\nErik Eidesen from the Byplan office in Troms\u00f8 thanks Roger for clarifying the issue regarding the agreement with PIF for the Fjellheisplat\u00e5et. Byplan will address this internally as soon as possible and Margareth will keep them informed. Erik Eidesen also reminds that all emails to Troms\u00f8 kommune are subject to the Public Information Act.\n\nErik Eidesen from Byplan office thanks for clarifying the issue and assures that they will follow up on it internally as soon as possible. Margareth will keep everyone informed regarding the matter. Roger Fagerheim from Fjellheisen AS discusses the challenges in the agreement with PIF regarding the development of the plateau. There was an initial agreement for cost sharing and collaboration, but PIF now wants to shift more of the costs to Fjellheisen. Fjellheisen AS believes this is unfair and requests for the issue to be resolved promptly to avoid any delays in the construction project.This email exchange discusses the detailed regulation of the mountain lift, with a specific focus on the upper station. The communication indicates that no traffic management requirements are being placed on the lower station at this time, as the municipality had previously granted permission for its renovation. There is also mention of ongoing dialogue between the municipality and other relevant parties regarding handling traffic challenges.Planlegging av transport av anleggsmaskiner for Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon i Troms\u00f8 krever n\u00f8ye vurdering av motorferdselloven. Et forslag til etablering av en midlertidig anleggsvei har blitt diskutert og det er viktig \u00e5 koordinere dette med planprosessen for \u00e5 unng\u00e5 ulemper for friluftslivet, KULA-omr\u00e5det, naturmangfoldet og reindrifta. Transporten p\u00e5 barmark m\u00e5 ogs\u00e5 f\u00f8lge reglene i motorferdselloven og det vurderes at etablering av en anleggsvei vil utl\u00f8se reguleringsplikt. Til slutt blir det opplyst om hvem som er ansvarlige myndigheter og kontaktpersoner for ytterligere informasjon om motorferdsellovverket.Heidi Holmstr\u00f8m from Mattilsynet is requesting specific attachments related to a project for Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon for review. The requested attachments are missing from the documents received and she is asking for them to be sent to her with the reference number 2023/18894.Lars Hamran is requesting clarification on a few points regarding the regulatory plan for the mountain lift project, including the placement of a security fence and the interpretation of building regulations. He suggests discussing these issues in a meeting or via email with Margareth Sundf\u00f8r.Lars Hamran has reviewed all incoming comments and preliminary investigations are underway for Plan 1956 Fjellheisen. He is requesting a meeting soon to discuss the next steps and has proposed a timeline that includes a committee meeting before summer. He is asking Margareth Sundf\u00f8r to suggest a suitable time for the meeting.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r confirms that physical meetings are preferred for the upcoming project kickoff meeting, and suggests holding it at the town hall for one hour instead of two. She also proposes a site visit after the meeting. She schedules the kickoff meeting for December 8th at 10 am and will send out the meeting invitation later in the day. Lars Hamran, an architect, agrees with the plan and confirms that all suggested times work for him.Lars Hamran is following up on a meeting request regarding Plan 1956 Fjellheisen, and wants to discuss the setting of plan boundaries, draft plan provisions, a progress plan, and how received feedback may impact the planning process. They have provided a preliminary draft of comments on the feedback and attached relevant documents. Margareth Sundf\u00f8r from Troms\u00f8 kommune requests more information before the meeting, including the progress plan and all feedback received, as well as a proposal for a meeting agenda. Additionally, Lars Hamran suggests a meeting before the summer and asks Sundf\u00f8r to suggest a suitable time.Margareth Sundfr, an area planner at Troms\u00f8 municipality, informs Roger Fagerheim of Frabene AS about the deadline for comments on the proposed regulation plan for Fjellheisen vre stasjon. The deadline is set for January 11, 2024, with an 8-week consultation period. Sundfr apologizes for not including Frabene AS on the recipient list but mentions that the proposal has been sent to Fjellheisen AS and Hamran/Johansen arkitekter AS. She provides a link to access all relevant documents and attachments. Sundfr also mentions that a supplementary proposal was approved during the KOBY meeting.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r sent an email to Roger Fagerheim, Kristian, Lars Hamran, and Ole regarding the final meeting minutes from the meeting on September 21 about the detailed regulation of the Fjellheisen upper station. She thanked them for their feedback and attached the final meeting minutes and presentation. She mentioned that most of the feedback was incorporated into the minutes with some minor adjustments, except for the suggestion that the plan boundary should be finalized before the neighborhood meeting. Sundf\u00f8r explained the background for this decision over the phone on September 26. She signed off as an urban planner at the Troms\u00f8 Municipality and provided her contact information. She also mentioned that all emails to Troms\u00f8 Municipality are subject to public disclosure.Rigmor Tonstad forwarded an email dialogue to Margareth Sundf\u00f8r regarding the Fjellheisen project process. Roger Fagerheim expressed concern about creating a plan initiative without aligning expectations and emphasized the importance of working closely together from the beginning for an efficient process.\n\nRoger mener at det vil v\u00e6re fornuftig \u00e5 ha et m\u00f8te for \u00e5 g\u00e5 gjennom hva som skal v\u00e6re en del av planinitiativet og diskutere faser og framdrift i planarbeidet. Han h\u00e5per at m\u00f8tet kan finne sted s\u00e5 raskt som mulig.\n\nRoger expresses concern about moving towards a traditional track in the planning process and suggests working closely together on the project from the beginning to make the process as efficient as possible. He proposes a meeting to review what should be included in the planning initiative, discuss phases and progress in the planning process, and hopes to schedule this meeting quickly. Rigmor responds that they cannot meet the next day but recommends promptly developing a plan initiative as a basis for the planning process. She asks for an indication of when this will be ready so they can schedule a meeting to review and clarify the process further.Hamran/Johansen Arkitekter AS has started the detailed planning process for the development of Fjellstua and outdoor areas on the mountain lift plateau in Troms\u00f8. The purpose of the plan is to confirm land use at the upper station and mountain lodge, facilitate new construction, and develop outdoor areas towards Storsteinen. The plan has been assessed in relation to environmental impact regulations and does not fall under them. Comments on the plan can be submitted to the architect's office in Oslo by February 15, 2023.\n\nPlaninitiativ Fjellheisen omfatter detaljregulering for nybygg til Fjellstua og utomhusomr\u00e5der p\u00e5 eiendommene 17, 1473, 1475, 1, 6 og 11. Etter en forutg\u00e5ende prosess med s\u00f8knad om rammetillatelse og dispensasjon, er det n\u00e5 besluttet at tiltaket m\u00e5 gjennom en detaljregulering. Bakgrunnen for dette er at det har v\u00e6rt endringer i eierskapet av anlegget og behov for modifikasjoner i byggeplanene. Planinitiativet skal danne rammer og prosess for privat detaljregulering i samsvar med plan- og bygningsloven.\n\nForskriften om behandling av private forslag til detaljregulering etter plan- og bygningsloven \u00a71 krever en redegj\u00f8relse for form\u00e5let med planen og planomr\u00e5det. Form\u00e5let med planen er \u00e5 stadfeste etablert arealbruk p\u00e5 \u00f8vre stasjon og Fjellstua, samt \u00e5 legge til rette for nybygg og opparbeiding av utomhusarealene mot Storsteinen. Planomr\u00e5det omfatter eiendommene 17/1473 og -1475, med deler av andre eiendommer inkludert som friomr\u00e5de. Planens grenser er satt slik at den kun omfatter omr\u00e5der n\u00f8dvendige for gjennomf\u00f8ring av planlagte tiltak.\n\nHamran/Johansen Arkitekter AS planlegger \u00e5 bygge et nytt bygg for \u00f8vre stasjon og Fjellstua samt opparbeide utomhusanlegget i planomr\u00e5det. Adkomst til Fjellstua skjer via gondolbanen eller til fots, spesielt fra Sherpatrappa. Det legges vekt p\u00e5 universell utforming med tilgjengelighet for alle, markerte snuarealer og tilpasninger for svaksynte. Den tekniske prosjekteringen vil bli ansvarsbelagt i forbindelse med s\u00f8knad om igangsettingstillatelse. \u00d8vre stasjon ligger p\u00e5 421 moh. med utsikt over Troms\u00f8.\n\nI 2016 ble det installert nye gondoler i de gamle bygningene, noe som har \u00f8kt passasjertallet kraftig. De gamle bygningene er n\u00e5 for sm\u00e5 til \u00e5 h\u00e5ndtere antallet passasjerer, og en ny stasjon med klar identitet som adkomst til fjellet er under planlegging. Taket p\u00e5 den nye stasjonen er utformet b\u00e5de funksjonelt for \u00e5 passe bygningens form\u00e5l og estetisk for \u00e5 assosiere til fjellandskapet. Materialvalget er r\u00e5 og ubehandlet for \u00e5 passe inn i naturen, med hovedkonstruksjon i limtre. B\u00e6ringen for glasset vil v\u00e6re i limtrestolper i stedet for aluminium. Nye Fjellstua vil v\u00e6re et moderne og kvalitetsfokusert bygg tilpasset dagens behov.\n\nProsjektet har fokus p\u00e5 milj\u00f8, b\u00e6rekraft og tilgjengelighet for alle ved fjellheisplat\u00e5et i Troms\u00f8. Tiltakene skal forbedre sikkerheten og kanalisere gangtrafikken for \u00e5 redusere slitasje p\u00e5 naturen. M\u00e5let er \u00e5 ivareta naturkvaliteter, forhindre forringelse av naturen og gj\u00f8re omr\u00e5det tilgjengelig for bevegelseshemmede gjennom bruk av robuste materialer og opparbeidelse av stier.\n\nThe accessibility between Fjellstua and Storsteinen is being improved for wheelchair users and visually impaired individuals. The Fjellheisen is a vital option for those who cannot access the mountains in other ways, so the area should be developed for maximum enjoyment for all. Measures will be taken to minimize wear and tear on the natural environment, with designated paths and seating areas. The Fjellheisplat\u00e5et is a key point for popular hiking trails, so efforts will be made to prevent off-path walking. The Fjellheisplat\u00e5et is Troms\u00f8's main tourist attraction and the most popular hiking destination, with visitor numbers increasing in recent years due to the Sherpatrappa.\n\nN\u00e5r prosjektet er gjennomf\u00f8rt, vil Fjellheisplat\u00e5et v\u00e6re attraktivt for alle typer brukere og sikre at det forblir attraktivt for fremtiden. Sikkerheten mot stupet vil bli forbedret ved \u00e5 etablere rekkverk. Byggets plassering og funksjon indikerer at det skal v\u00e6re synlig som et signalbygg, men samtidig harmonere godt med landskapet. Det planlagte nybygget vil ha en st\u00f8rre bruttoareal enn det eksisterende bygget og vil fremst\u00e5 som en del av landskapet fra \u00f8versiden.\n\nThe existing building is old and has undergone multiple changes without an overall plan, resulting in a building that is ineffective in terms of aesthetics, function, and universal design. The new building aims to address these issues and improve energy efficiency. The outdoor area will also be redesigned to improve safety, protect vegetation, and enhance the overall area. The building will be designed to blend with the surrounding landscape and prioritize environmental sustainability. Public participation, potential risks, and considerations for social, economic, and environmental sustainability are also outlined.Adresse: R\u00e5dhusgata 2, 9008 Troms\u00f8, Postboks 6900 Langnes, 9299 Troms\u00f8, Telefon: 77 79 00 00, E-post: postmottak@tromso.kommune.no. Referat fra naboskapsm\u00f8te for plan 1956 detaljregulering for Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon ble gjennomf\u00f8rt med deltakelse fra ulike parter. Det ble gitt en kort orientering om planprosessen og viktigheten av \u00e5 komme med innspill tidlig i planarbeidet.\n\nTroms\u00f8 kommune har presentert detaljreguleringen for Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon, som best\u00e5r av to prosjekter: et nytt bygg og tilrettelegging av uteomr\u00e5det. Kommunen planlegger \u00e5 utvikle plat\u00e5et for \u00e5 opprettholde bes\u00f8kstallet og gj\u00f8re omr\u00e5det tilgjengelig for personer med nedsatt funksjonsevne. Forprosjektet fokuserte p\u00e5 tilgjengelighet, sikkerhet, reparasjon av slitasje, og skape opplevelser. Innspill og merknader kan sendes til postmottak@tromso.kommune.no merket med \"Innspill plan 1956 Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon.\"\n\nSummary: The Fjellheisen upper station and Fjellstua were established in 1961 and now require building upgrades. The area is currently not regulated but designated for LNFR purposes in the municipal land use plan. A neighbor meeting was held to discuss the detailed planning for the Fjellheisen upper station, including plans for a new building and outdoor area improvements. The new building will be larger and constructed with environmentally friendly materials to accommodate various functions. Questions were raised about winter maintenance, existing playgrounds, transport logistics, and agreements with landowners. Plans are also underway to upgrade the bottom station, with helicopter transport planned for construction materials.Dette referatet handler om et m\u00f8te mellom Troms\u00f8 kommune, Avinor og Statsforvalteren ang\u00e5ende implementering av bestemmelser om birdstrike i reguleringsplaner. Det har v\u00e6rt vanskelig \u00e5 komme til enighet om dette, og diskusjonen inkluderer hvordan man kan h\u00e5ndtere birdstrike problematikken p\u00e5 en effektiv m\u00e5te. Det ble foresl\u00e5tt \u00e5 se p\u00e5 bestemmelsen p\u00e5 overordnet niv\u00e5, samt \u00e5 oppdatere ROS-analyser og inkludere birdstrike i kommunale beredskapsplaner. Dette m\u00f8tet fokuserte p\u00e5 \u00e5 finne en l\u00f8sning p\u00e5 tvisten og videre handlingsplan.Lars Hamran sent a revised plan initiative to Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, but later realized there were internal disagreements and will need to send another revision at a later time. He apologized for the premature sending and mentioned that he will provide a preliminary feedback in a separate email.The document is regarding a proposal for a detailed regulation plan for Fjellheisen's upper station in Troms\u00f8. The fee for this proposal is set at NOK 99,900 according to Troms\u00f8 municipality's fee regulations. The document also outlines additional fees for different aspects of the project and specifies that payment is required for any changes to the regulation plan. The fees will be invoiced separately, and the document is signed by Erik Eidesen and Margareth Sundf\u00f8r from the Department of Urban Development.The email raises concerns about the lack of traffic management measures in relation to the development of the upper station of the Fjellheisen cable car in Troms\u00f8. The sender, who lives nearby, argues for the inclusion of traffic flow requirements in the development plan to address the existing issues with traffic congestion in the area. They also echo the concerns of Troms County Council regarding the potential negative impact of the project on public transport infrastructure. They indicate that further comments may be provided in the future.The email outlines the challenges in reaching an agreement with PIF regarding the development of the mountain lift plateau. Despite previous discussions and agreements on cost-sharing, PIF is now unwilling to split the costs of development. The email requests clarification from the City Development management on the situation due to tight project timelines. The sender emphasizes the urgency of resolving the issue promptly to avoid delays in construction.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r suggests a brief meeting on Teams to discuss some issues she has discovered regarding the degree of exploitation in the regulatory plan for the mountain lift. She apologizes for giving incorrect information and references a specific paragraph in a guideline. She advises checking with the building department on how to interpret the calculation rules. Lars Hamran responds with revised plans and questions about adjusting boundaries to accommodate safety fences within specified areas. He also seeks clarification on interpreting calculation rules for exploitation levels, specifically relating to open covered areas and volume-heavy constructions. He proposes discussing these matters at the scheduled meeting or by email if more convenient.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r is following up on a phone conversation regarding the ROS analysis for the Plan 1956 Fjellheisen \u00f8vre station. She notes that the feedback from the municipality on the analysis in June has not been adequately addressed in the plan proposal sent in September. She requests that Hamran/Johansen Arkitekter AS sends a response to the municipality's points on the ROS analysis along with a note from an expert by September 25. Due to the incomplete nature of the plan proposal, the meeting scheduled for October 2 will likely be postponed to October 16. Margeth also mentions the possibility of revising the ROS analysis and asks for updates on when a revised version could be expected.NVE gir generelle innspill til Troms\u00f8 kommune ang\u00e5ende en detaljreguleringsplan for Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon. De gir veiledning om hvordan deres saksomr\u00e5der skal ivaretas i planen, og minner kommunen om sitt ansvar for \u00e5 ta hensyn til flom- og skredfare, vassdrag og energianlegg i arealplaner. NVE har begrenset kapasitet og vil prioritere \u00e5 gi hjelp til de kommunene som har st\u00f8rst behov.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r has sent an email to Lars Hamran with a list of landowners and stakeholders for Plan 1956. She reminds Lars to consider notifying additional landowners if the plan area is expanded. Meeting feedback and agreements are being reviewed and will be sent to Lars soon. Margareth is an urban planner at Troms\u00f8 municipality. Email communication with Troms\u00f8 municipality is subject to the Public Access to Information Act.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an urban planner for Troms\u00f8 kommune, has sent an email to inform about the public review of proposal plan 1956 for the upper station of Fjellheisen. The documents can be found on the municipality's website and the deadline for comments is January 11, 2024. Contact information for further inquiries is provided.Kommunen oversender referat fra oppstartsm\u00f8tet for plan 1956 Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon. Det ble diskutert muligheten for overnatting p\u00e5 Fjellheisplat\u00e5et, behovet for oppm\u00e5ling av eiendomsgrenser og planer for opparbeiding av uteomr\u00e5det. Kommunen mener at \u00e5 legge til rette for overnatting vil kreve endringer i planarbeidet. Kommunen informerer ogs\u00e5 om hvor man kan finne informasjon om n\u00f8yaktighet av eiendomsgrenser og hvordan man kan kontakte geodata for sp\u00f8rsm\u00e5l knyttet til oppm\u00e5ling. Planer for opparbeiding av uteomr\u00e5det er ogs\u00e5 omtalt, med en foresl\u00e5tt budsjettbehandling i kommunestyret.The neighborhood meeting at Fjellheisen Upper Station scheduled for October 19th has been postponed, as per a message from management. A new date will be proposed soon. Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, area planner from the Urban Development Section, will inform Lars Hamran once the new time is confirmed.Gaute Sletteland from Statsforvalteren has requested an extension for the deadline for a response to Margareth Wegner Sundfoer regarding the plan 1956 detaljregulering for Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon. He asks for confirmation via email that the deadline is extended until January 17th, with the response to be sent to the municipality by January 18th.Roger Fagerheim is inquiring about the progress of the agreement with PIF regarding Fjellheisplat\u00e5et. He expresses concern about a newspaper article that may have given a misleading impression about Fjellheisen's intentions regarding a new access road. Roger Fagerheim is the managing director of Frabene AS.\n\nRoger is following up on the issue of the agreement with PIF regarding the Fjellheisplat\u00e5et. He expresses concern about a recent news article that may have given the wrong impression about Fjellheisen's plans for an access road. He hopes that residents in Tromsdalen are not unnecessarily worried. Margareth will keep them informed and Byplan will address the issue internally as soon as possible.\n\nRoger Fagerheim from Frabene AS is expressing frustration in an email to Troms\u00f8 Municipality regarding challenges in reaching an agreement with PIF for the development of the mountain cable car plateau. Despite previously agreed terms, PIF is now unwilling to share the costs for development, which may delay the project. Fagerheim urges for a swift resolution to ensure timely construction start in 2024.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an area planner at Troms\u00f8 Municipality, sent an email regarding the plan for the upper station of Fjellheisen. She attached the requested plan boundaries as a SOSI file and PDF printout and mentioned that the plan is also registered in the municipality's plan register. The email also included contact information and a reminder that all correspondence to Troms\u00f8 Municipality is subject to public disclosure.The document is a letter regarding a proposed detailed regulation for Fjellheisen in Troms\u00f8 municipality. The plan involves converting the area into a building zone to improve year-round use, safety, and accessibility. The letter highlights the importance of considering reindeer herding, cultural heritage, and minimizing landscape impacts in the planning process. The Sami Parliament requests involvement in further procedures, and the Troms\u00f8 municipality is suggested to coordinate signage with information about cultural heritage and reindeer herding. The letter also mentions an opinion from Troms and Finnmark County Council.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, area planner, sent a email to Roger Fagerheim with a complaint received regarding the decision on the detailed regulation of the upper station of Fjellheisen. She attached the complaint as discussed over the phone. The email also includes her contact information and a note that all emails to Troms\u00f8 municipality are subject to the Public Administration Act and may be made public.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r provides an update on a meeting regarding Plan 1956 for the Fjellheisen upper station, specifically regarding the safety zone in a report. Skred AS will update a previous note to explain why the safety zone in the NGI report is not relevant for the detailed planning of the upper station. The municipality does not see the need to expand the plan to include planned avalanche protection for the lower station. The plan will be presented at a coordination meeting on October 16th. Sundf\u00f8r will schedule a meeting to review revised plan documents between October 2nd and 16th.Troms Fylkeskommune gir sin uttalelse til h\u00f8ringen om detaljregulering for Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon i Troms\u00f8 kommune. De fokuserer p\u00e5 viktigheten av \u00e5 ivareta interesser som kulturminner, friluftsliv, og klima- og milj\u00f8vennlige l\u00f8sninger i planleggingen. De \u00f8nsker at Troms\u00f8 kommune benytter bestemmelser som fremmer slike l\u00f8sninger og gir anbefalinger i forhold til klima, Samferdsel, kulturarv og friluftsliv. De ber ogs\u00e5 om en egen forvaltningsplan for fjellplat\u00e5et rundt fjellheisen for \u00e5 sikre b\u00e6rekraftig utvikling og oppf\u00f8lging av tiltakene i planen.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an urban planner, responded to Lars Hamran's concern about a provision in a report suggesting no mechanical snow removal in certain areas to protect vegetation. She emphasized the need for consistency between planning reports and proposals, as well as addressing the potential impact on safety and vegetation. Sundf\u00f8r advised clarifying the decision in the proposal to avoid it being returned for further information. Hamran had questioned the practicality and legality of the snow removal restriction.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r from the City Planning Department sent an email to Lars Hamran on September 11, 2023, regarding the revised Risk and Vulnerability Analysis (ROS) for the Fjellheisen upper station project. She raised concerns about the lack of explanation for the limited incorporation of feedback from a previous letter in June. Lars had forwarded the updated ROS analysis on September 8, but Margareth emphasized the need for a complete plan with an updated ROS analysis. She included the latest version of the ROS analysis, highlighting areas for revision. The email chain also included communications between Lars, Andre Johansen, and Pia Nordb\u00f8 from Multiconsult about the revision of the ROS analysis.This document is a Rigg- and Marksikringsplan for the Fjellheisen Regulering project with project number 22105. It includes details such as the scale, format, and safety measures for the construction site, including brakkers, a helipad, tower crane foundation, construction fence, storage space, avalanche protection, and more. The document also emphasizes the importance of proper lighting to avoid safety hazards during the construction period.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r suggests specifying in the title of the advertisement that it pertains to the upper station of the Fjellheisen. The municipality is open to parallel processing of the detailed regulation and building permit if the developer wishes, with Margareth serving as the contact person for both. However, the municipality is not equipped for efficient parallel processing due to a lack of provisions in the delegation regulations.\n\nKommunen er \u00e5pen for parallell behandling av detaljregulering og byggesak p\u00e5 Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon, men det er viktig at utbygger er klar over risikoen og at kommunen ikke er optimalt rigget for denne prosessen. Kommunen vil ikke dispensere for igangsetting av deler av tiltaket underveis. Utbygger m\u00e5 ta ansvar for eventuelle kostnader ved omprosjektering. Arealplanleggeren fungerer som kontaktperson for b\u00e5de detaljregulering og byggesaken.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an area planner, received a notice about the start of detailed planning for project 1956 for the Fjellheisen upper station. She notes that the letter was only addressed to the municipality and wonders if others received it as well. She mentions that the municipality will not respond to the notice as their feedback was given in a previous meeting and is documented in the meeting minutes. Sundf\u00f8r also points out missing documents that should have been included with the notice, according to the municipality's planning guidelines.Avinor AS has provided feedback on a proposed development plan for the upper station of the Fjellheisen cable car in Troms\u00f8. They have confirmed that the plan does not pose any obstacles to air navigation or pose a birdstrike risk. Avinor requests that certain preventive measures be included in the development plan to minimize the risk of bird strikes. They also mention that the proposed building does not require obstruction lights and is shielded by surrounding terrain. If their recommendations are not considered in the final plan, Avinor may take additional measures during the public consultation process.Marijne Janssens from Arkitektkontoret Amundsen AS is contacting Margareth Sundf\u00f8r from Troms\u00f8 kommune regarding the regulation plan for the upper station of Fjellheisen. They are requesting the plankart in dwg-format to understand the regulated zones. Margareth Sundf\u00f8r states that they do not provide dwg-files without agreement from the planner or developer, Fjellheisen AS. She suggests contacting Roger Fagerheim for further clarification on sharing the dwg-file.This document outlines regulations for the detailed regulation plan for the upper station of the Fjellheisen cable car, including establishing land use and new construction guidelines. The plan aims to facilitate outdoor areas towards Storsteinen, ensuring accessibility to the plateau and accommodating various recreational activities. Common regulations for the entire area include requirements for documentation when applying for building permits, such as demonstrating consideration for landscape aesthetics and providing an outdoor area plan.\n\nDokumentet er reguleringsbestemmelser for en detaljreguleringsplan for Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon. Hensikten er \u00e5 fastsette plan for arealbruk og legge til rette for nybygg, samt tilrettelegge utomhusarealene mot Storsteinen for turisme og rekreasjon. Fellesbestemmelser inkluderer krav til dokumentasjon ved s\u00f8knad om rammetillatelse, blant annet for skj\u00f8nnhetshensyn og uteromsplan i m\u00e5lestokk 1:200.\n\nThe application for a commencement permit must include documentation that technical detailed plans have been approved by the municipality's responsible technical department. An activity plan must also be submitted detailing how the surroundings will be protected during construction, including noise and other disturbances, machinery placement, traffic management, mass transport, pedestrian and cyclist safety, cleanliness, dust suppression, and noise levels. Necessary protective measures must be in place before construction begins. To ensure environmental conditions during construction, air quality and noise levels must comply with the Ministry of the Environment's guidelines. For an application for an occupancy permit and completion, an acceptance protocol signed by the municipality's responsible technical department and an approved water and sewage completion notification must be included.\n\nGenerelle bestemmelser som angir form\u00e5l, h\u00f8yde, atkomst og hensynssoner er angitt p\u00e5 plankartet. Det er krav til universell utforming, estetisk utforming og terrengbehandling. Ved s\u00f8knad om igangsettingstillatelse m\u00e5 dokumentasjon for godkjente tekniske detaljplaner og en anleggplan for beskyttelse av omgivelsene mot st\u00f8y og andre ulemper legges ved. Luftkvalitets- og st\u00f8ygrenser m\u00e5 f\u00f8lge Milj\u00f8verndepartementets retningslinjer for behandling av luftkvalitet og st\u00f8y i arealplanleggingen.\n\nTiltakshavere som skal opparbeide offentlige samferdselsanlegg, teknisk infrastruktur og gr\u00f8nnstruktur m\u00e5 legge ved en overtakelsesprotokoll signert av kommunens fagorgan ved s\u00f8knad om midlertidig brukstillatelse og ferdigattest. I tillegg m\u00e5 en godkjent VA-ferdigmelding legges ved s\u00f8knaden. Andre fellesbestemmelser inkluderer forhold som skal vises p\u00e5 plankartet, funksjons- og kvalitetskrav, byggeh\u00f8yde og hensyn til verneverdier som kulturmilj\u00f8 og naturmangfold. Offentlige samferdselsanlegg, teknisk infrastruktur, og gr\u00f8nnstruktur skal opparbeides i tr\u00e5d med planbestemmelser og kommunale normer, og eventuelle eksisterende anlegg m\u00e5 oppgraderes i samsvar med disse normene. Tekniske detaljplaner m\u00e5 godkjennes av kommunens fagorgan f\u00f8r utbygging kan starte.\n\nTekniske detaljplaner for vann, avl\u00f8p og overvann m\u00e5 f\u00f8lge VAO-rammeplanen og eventuelle avvik kan kreve revisjon av rammeplanen og endringer i reguleringsplanen. Eventuelle funn av gjenstander eller spor av eldre aktivitet under byggeprosessen m\u00e5 rapporteres umiddelbart til relevant myndighet. Byggeh\u00f8yder, verneverdier, infrastruktur og gr\u00f8ntarealer m\u00e5 f\u00f8lge de gjeldende normer og planer for omr\u00e5det.\n\nTechnical detailed plans for water, sewage, and stormwater must be developed in accordance with the VAO framework plan and acceptance letter. Any deviations between the technical detailed plans and the VAO framework plan may require revisions to the VAO framework plan and changes to the zoning plan. Additionally, the plans should coordinate solutions from the VAO framework plan and OSG framework plan. Any findings of objects or traces of older activities during construction must be reported to the appropriate authorities. Specific regulations and requirements are outlined for different types of land use, such as buildings and facilities, green spaces, and agricultural areas. Provisions are also made for hazard zones, high-voltage facilities, and the order in which approvals must be obtained before use. Additionally, the documents that hold legal significance through references in the regulations are specified.The email chain discusses a revision of the Risk and Vulnerability Analysis (ROS) for Fjellheisen AS, with a PDF of the report attached. There is a clarification of existing details rather than new information. Pia Nordb\u00f8 from Multiconsult is working on the revision, focusing on the details about fences. Andr\u00e9 Johansen confirms that the text is sufficient and may be included in the plan description.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r confirms that not all attachments were included in the previous email and provides a link to where they can be found on the municipality's website. Jon Gunnar Blom requests specifically for the missing attachment regarding the KULA-landscape and asks for it to be sent to him.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an urban planner at Troms\u00f8 kommune, is questioning whether noise forecasts have been created for the transportation of construction materials and waste for plan 1956 Fjellheisen \u00f8vre. She notes that the plan description does not seem to include noise forecasts as stated in response to a comment from the State Administration. Sundf\u00f8r suggests a simple adjustment to the comment to address this issue. She contacts Andre Severin Johansen and Lars Hamran for clarification before making any changes.Christina Joakimsen from Troms fylkeskommune is requesting an extension for the consultation deadline for the Fjellheisen local plan to be moved to Monday, January 15th. She hopes for a positive response from Margareth Sundf\u00f8r from Troms\u00f8 kommune.Detaljregulering for Fjellheisen \u00f8vre stasjon ble vedtatt av kommunestyret og kan p\u00e5klages til Statsforvalteren. Klagefristen er 3 uker fra mottak av brevet. Informasjon om erstatning og innl\u00f8sning av eiendommer gis, og saken kan ses p\u00e5 kommunens nettside. Vedlegg inkluderer saksprotokoll og planbeskrivelser. Klager kan sendes til kommunen, med mulighet for \u00e5 be om begrunnelse og utsatt iverksetting av vedtaket. Rett til \u00e5 se dokumenter og kostnader knyttet til klagesaken blir ogs\u00e5 nevnt.Lars Hamran suggests holding a neighborhood meeting via Teams on October 19th at 18:00 and asks for input on the meeting's details. Margareth Sundf\u00f8r from the municipality confirms that neighborhood meetings are typically held on Teams and provides possible dates for the meeting. She also asks for clarification on who the contact person for the municipality is in the planning process.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r informs Roger Fagerheim that they have received six comments on the proposed plan and that the deadline for the comments was extended. She will review the comments in the coming week and suggests the possibility of a meeting. Roger Fagerheim requests the comments and expresses eagerness to see them.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r is requesting a noise analysis for the upper station of a project and notes that further revisions may be needed. Lars Hamran, the architect, responds that no additional analysis has been done beyond what was previously stated. There is also a mention of revising a comment related to noise issues that were not addressed in the initial assessment.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r from Troms\u00f8 kommune inquired about the shuttle bus service from the city center to Fjellheisen lower station. Ulf Johansen, the manager of Fjellheisen, responded that the shuttle bus service had stopped on October 1st due to poor demand. However, they plan to resume the service fully during the summer and winter seasons. They acknowledge the need and plan to promote it better.The email is informing Margareth Sundf\u00f8r that the minutes from the meeting on February 2, 2024, regarding Plan 1956 Fjellheisen Upper Station have been finalized and are attached to the email.Lars Hamran is informing Margareth Sundf\u00f8r about the plan to deliver a complete plan proposal for the Fjellheisen upper station on the agreed deadline. There are difficulties with the pre-approval of the VAO framework plan, as the saksbehandler is currently on sick leave, putting them in a challenging situation. Lars asks if they can submit the plan proposal without the approved framework plan and send it later. He also offers to send some materials for review before the delivery date. They have arranged for geodata to produce the map in SOSI format.Lars Hamran forwarded a draft of a map and regulations to Margareth Sundf\u00f8r for their upcoming meeting on the 28th. He requested feedback on the material before the meeting and provided his contact information for further communication.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r has confirmed that the dwg file can be shared with Marijne Janssens. Irene Johansen also confirms that the message with the attachment is ready to be sent.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r is inquiring about the concept sketch for the collaborative project in the plan for the Fjellheisen upper station. She is questioning whether the attachment labeled as the outdoor illustration project in Attachment 14 is the concept sketch for the collaboration. She requests clarification on which document serves as the concept sketch for the project.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r from Troms\u00f8 kommune is informing Andre Johansen and others that the municipality has decided not to allow the depositing/reuse of excavated materials in a public outdoor space due to environmental concerns. Andre Johansen disagrees with this decision and questions the municipality's plan to acquire special expertise for rehabilitating vegetation in the area. He also references a report by the Environmental Directorate on responsible reuse of excavated materials. They plan to discuss further on Friday.Lars Hamran sent a brief meeting summary to Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, suggesting a physical meeting for their upcoming project. He provided multiple time options for the meeting and signed off as an architect from HAMRAN/JOHANSEN ARKITEKTER AS.Statsforvalteren i Troms og Finnmark varsler om oppstart av detaljregulering for fjellheisen i Troms\u00f8 kommune. Form\u00e5let er \u00e5 stadfeste arealbruk p\u00e5 \u00f8vre stasjon og fjellstua, samt legge til rette for nybygg. Eksisterende fjellstue skal rives og erstattes med nybygg. Planen inkluderer ogs\u00e5 opparbeiding av utomhusarealer for \u00f8kt sikkerhet og tilgjengelighet. Planomr\u00e5det er p\u00e5 ca. 100 dekar og vil ikke \u00f8ke aktiviteten p\u00e5 Fjellheisplat\u00e5et, men legger til rette for mer hel\u00e5rlig bruk.\n\nThe plan work will likely lead to an increase in visitors. Helicopter noise will be related to the construction period. The plan falls under the coordination task of the State Administration, giving them the authority to coordinate and potentially reject objections from government agencies. The municipality has determined that the plan does not require an impact assessment under the Environmental Impact Assessment Regulation. They believe the plan will not have a significant impact on the environment or society compared to the current situation. The plan will allow for year-round use and may attract more visitors, leading to potential traffic and parking challenges outside the planned area.\n\nStatsforvalteren erkjenner at \u00f8kende bes\u00f8kende til Fjellstua kan f\u00f8re til trafikkproblemer, men kommunen mener at dette m\u00e5 l\u00f8ses etter andre prosesser enn regulering. Det er uklart hva disse prosessene inneb\u00e6rer, men trafikk og samferdsel m\u00e5 fortsatt tas hensyn til i planarbeidet. Statsforvalteren stiller sp\u00f8rsm\u00e5l ved gjennomf\u00f8ringen av detaljregulering uten \u00e5 l\u00f8se trafikkproblemer, og mener at en mulig \u00f8kning i trafikk grunnet bes\u00f8kende kan v\u00e6re et argument for en konsekvensutredning. Til tross for dette har Statsforvalteren kommet frem til at det ikke er n\u00f8dvendig med en konsekvensutredning i denne saken. Det m\u00e5 likevel gj\u00f8res grundige vurderinger av ulike forhold i planarbeidet p\u00e5 grunn av omr\u00e5dets beskaffenhet og Fjellstuas identitet.\n\nStatsforvalteren st\u00f8tter kommunens vurderinger og forventer grundige utredninger av kulturhistorisk landskap, trua arter eller naturtyper, og friluftsliv i planarbeidet. De p\u00e5peker at h\u00e5ndtering av st\u00f8y i anleggsfasen, spesielt i forbindelse med frakt av materialer med helikopter, vil v\u00e6re viktig og viser til retningslinjer for behandling av st\u00f8y i arealplanleggingen. De oppfordrer til utarbeidelse av en plan for h\u00e5ndtering av st\u00f8y i bygge- og anleggsfasen som inkluderer prognoser for st\u00f8yniv\u00e5er og st\u00f8yutbredelse.\n\nStatsforvalteren \u00f8nsker at prognosene skal beskrive st\u00f8yforholdene i perioden, inkludert tidspunkt for aktivitet, st\u00f8yniv\u00e5er, st\u00f8yutbredelse og antall ber\u00f8rte. Det er viktig \u00e5 ha avb\u00f8tende tiltak for \u00e5 redusere st\u00f8yniv\u00e5ene. Videre m\u00e5 planen ta hensyn til truede arter og naturtyper i omr\u00e5det, og utbygging b\u00f8r lokaliseres til omr\u00e5der med minst konflikt. Det anbefales \u00e5 utrede effektene p\u00e5 naturmangfoldet og landskapet, og medvirkning fra allmennheten b\u00f8r v\u00e6re en del av planprosessen. Det oppfordres til \u00e5 fokusere p\u00e5 FNs b\u00e6rekraftsm\u00e5l, spesielt m\u00e5l om ansvarlig forbruk og produksjon, og \u00e5 stoppe klimaendringene. Kommunen bes om \u00e5 sende planforslaget i SOSI-format f\u00f8r h\u00f8ring. Statsforvalteren er tilgjengelig for sp\u00f8rsm\u00e5l og dr\u00f8ftinger.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r suggests including a provision in the detailed regulation requiring a plan for handling noise during construction before a permit is granted. This provision is mandated by the planning and building law and cannot be waived. She also mentions that construction noise, including helicopter noise, should be addressed in the regulation regardless. Lars Hamran inquires about including a provision for a noise assessment in the construction phase, as suggested by Multiconsult.Lars Hamran is emailing Margareth Sundf\u00f8r regarding the creation of an outdoor space plan in a 1:1000 scale instead of the required 1:500 scale. He asks if it would be acceptable to have some sections in the larger scale due to the difficulty of handling the larger format. Sundf\u00f8r responds that she is working on a meeting summary but it won't be ready until after Easter. They exchange pleasantries and confirm the plan for sending the summary after the holiday.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an urban planner, is inquiring about the absence of noise impact assessments in the plan for the construction of the upper station of the Fjellheisen. She questions whether it was not included or if she overlooked it. She requests clarification from Lars Hamran regarding this matter.Rigmor Tonstad from the municipality of Troms\u00f8 sent a feedback letter regarding the incomplete proposal for plan 1956 Fjellheisen upper station. The proposal was not deemed ready for public hearing as it did not meet the necessary criteria and did not align with the guidelines set in a previous meeting. The letter included a checklist of points that needed to be addressed and suggested further collaboration with the city planning department. It was signed by Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, the leader of the planning section for urban development.Lars Hamran is writing to Margareth Sundf\u00f8r regarding the revision of a plan initiative for Fjellheisen. He references an email from PIF that clearly shows agreement on the proposed agreement. Lars believes there is no reason for the agreement, which has been worked on for a year, to be reconsidered due to detailed regulations.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an urban planner at Troms\u00f8 Municipality, informs Lars Hamran that they can submit their proposal by the end of the day on September 1st. She mentions that she will be working on the municipality's land use plan on Friday and won't be able to address the Fjellheisen project until Monday.Lars Hamran sent an email to Margareth Sundf\u00f8r attaching a draft advertisement for the Fjellheisen project and asking for feedback on whether anything else should be included. Lars is an architect at Hamran/Johansen Arkitekter AS.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r, an area planner for Troms\u00f8 kommune, has informed Lars Hamran that they can submit their complete plan proposal for the upper station of Fjellheisen next Friday, even without the approved VAO-rammeplan. She explains that the deadline for the municipality to decide on public review of the plan proposal will only begin once the proposal is complete. Lars Hamran, an architect, expresses concern about the delay in the approval of the VAO-rammeplan and asks if they can submit the plan proposal without it and send it afterwards. He also offers to send draft descriptions or provisions for review before submission.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r is following up on a meeting where a provision for architectural quality in building permits was discussed. The current proposal is considered too vague by the building department, who suggest including requirements for sloping roofs and specifying the highest and lowest height levels.Margareth Sundf\u00f8r reminds Lars Hamran about the need for the advertisement for the start of plan work to be approved by the municipality. She directs him to where he can find information on what should be included in the advertisement and points him to an example on the municipality's website. Sundf\u00f8r signs off as an urban planner for the city of Troms\u00f8."